idean Explorations,\" followed by an open&nbsp;discussion on the relationship between virtue ethics and law.&nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;JLSA will be providing lots and lots of delicious food&nbsp;and&nbsp;drinks, so be sure to stop by!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Bio: Rabbi Held has a PhD in religion from Harvard; his main academic interests are in modern Jewish and Christian thought and in the history of Zionism. A&nbsp;renowned lecturer and educator, he won&nbsp;the 2011 Covenant Award for excellence in Jewish education, and Newsweek has twice named him one of America&#39;s most influential rabbis. He is a co-founder of Mechon Hadar and the author of the recently released book, &lt;em&gt;Abraham Joshua Heschel: The Call of Transcendence&lt;/em&gt; (Indiana University Press, 2013).&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"Thu, 12 Mar 2015 12:30:00\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"30428\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:145;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"\n			\n			\n			\n			\n            \n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"(3/12/15) Innovation Policy Colloquium: Jason Du Mont\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:78:\"http://its.law.nyu.edu/eventcalendar/index.cfm?fuseaction=main.detail&id=37003\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:832:\"&lt;p&gt;The Innovation