INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1012,1,'2013-10-22 23:25:31','2013-10-23 03:25:31','<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/pta-october-general-meeting-mixer/ptamixer2013/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1013\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1013\" title=\"PTAMIXER2013\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/PTAMIXER2013-550x720.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"720\" /></a>\n\nCome and meet the fellow CWS parents, teachers, and hear about all the great things we do, and let your voices be heard. We look forward to seeing you there! For archives of PTA meeting minutes and information, please visit the office. Thank you.','PTA October General Meeting + Mixer','','publish','open','open','','pta-october-general-meeting-mixer','','','2013-10-22 23:25:31','2013-10-23 03:25:31','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1012',0,'post','',0),(1029,1,'2013-11-07 12:40:44','2013-11-07 17:40:44','<p align=\"center\"><b>The Children’s Workshop School Update</b></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><b>For November 2013</b></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://www.childrensworkshopschool.org/\">http://www.childrensworkshopschool.org</a></p>\n<p align=\"center\">917-324-5713 or 917-386-4798 or <a href=\"mailto:ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org\">ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org</a></p>\n<p align=\"center\">”We’re all a family under one sky!”</p>\n\n<table width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<table width=\"600\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=\"left\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">Thank you to Elizabeth and Rina for co-chairing the <b>Harvest Festival</b> and thank you to all the members of our school community for volunteering, contributing and participating: our admin/staff: Maria, Dorothy, Joyce, and Sonia; alumni mom Bev, who founded the Campos Garden and our local farmers; our custodial staff and school safety agents; our teachers, among them Molly, Miriam, Crystal, Jen, Susan, Gary, Suma, Helen, and Ms Capers; our parents: Nancy, Darryl, Jen, Rosie, David, Beth, Ally, Eric, Sean, Tiffany, Sayoko, Tomo, Richard, Tom, Marcia, Trina, Kasumi, Vanessa, Cassie, Kim, Mo, Shay and many, many more. We had a wonderful day of square dancing, arts and crafts, great food and gardening!</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n&nbsp;\n<table width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<table width=\"600\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=\"left\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">Thank you to Barbara Verrochi, her teachers and students at <b>The Shala Yoga Center</b>, on 11th Street and Broadway for raising $2000 so far for CWS to help us fund our Bent on Learning yoga program. The yoga fundraiser for our school will continue through the month of November. Take a class - bring a friend!</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n&nbsp;\n\nThank you to the <b>Technology Team</b> (Dorothy, our parent coordinator; teachers Jeff, Jessica, Susan, Crystal and Scott; parents Ian and Keiko) for hosting the evening Mixer/PTA meeting---and for obtaining grant funding through Councilwoman Rosie Mendez’s office so <b>that every classroom now has a smart board and we have 100 Mac Airbooks on 4 carts for our students to use.</b>\n\n<b>Thank you to the construction team for their beautiful work renovating the auditorium-</b>-it is so wonderful to be back in the auditorium for Friday Community Meetings!  As the word spreads, many CWS alumni have been stopping by to check it out.\n\nThank you to Joyce and Beverly for coordinating the <b>Kids Art notecard fundraiser</b>!  Next up is <b>Original Works</b>, this year coordinated by Jill, Nicole and Keiko—buy coffee mugs, magnets, etc with your child’s drawing on them.  Thanks to Jen for organizing Original Works for the past few years. Both Kids Art and Original Works donate a portion of your orders to fund our school programs.\n\nBe on the lookout for the <b>SCRIPP gift card fundraiser</b>, coordinated this year by Helen, Tiffany and Marcia:  order gift cards from stores that give our school a percentage of the gift card amount—use them for your holiday shopping!  Stores include Children’s Place, Payless, Macy’s, Land’s End, Starbucks and many more.\n\nThe <b>Winter Craft Fair will be Friday 13 December</b> in the lobby—with beautiful handmade jewelry, accessories, clothes, etc for sale—if you would like to be a vendor or have a vendor to recommend, please email Bari <a href=\"mailto:bari161@me.com\">bari161@me.com</a>\n\n<b>Congrats </b>to Rainie and Franny, both in Scott’s class:  they won the Lego Minecraft raffle.  It was Rainie again, who won the 50/50 Guess the Number of Pieces of Candy Corn in the Candy-Corn-Shaped-Sangria-Dispenser Raffle—Rainie guessed 3999 and the correct amount, counted by Melissa herself, was 3973.\n\n<b>November Raffle:</b>  Win 2 tickets to The Little Orchestra Society’s production of <b>Stravinsky’s <i>Firebird</i>,</b> beautifully staged with puppets and illumination, at City Center (55 St b/w 7<sup>th</sup> and 8<sup>th</sup>) on Sunday 24 November at 1pm—1 hour long, perfect for ages 4 and up.  <b>$2 per chance/3 chances for $5.</b>  Tickets will be sold at Coffee And… on 1 Nov, 8 Nov and 15 Nov with drawing on 15 Nov.\n\nThank you to Satya for volunteering to be <b>CWS Band Parent</b> and to Nicole for taking over the Book Fair from Melissa, who ran it for 4 years (thank you, Melissa).  This year’s <b>Barnes and Noble Book Fair </b>to benefit our lovely library will be over the weekend of 8 and 9 February with a theme of “Fall in Love with Reading.”\n\n<b>Class news:</b>  The fifth graders have started Golf at Chelsea Piers.  The third graders, as part of their study of Native Americans, are going to Inwood Hill Park soon to check out the ancient rock caves.  Elyssa and Michelle’s and Crystal’s classes  are coordinating <b>Penny Harvest</b>—please bring in your pennies (other change, even bills are accepted and welcome).\n\n<b>If you own a business or have a service to share with our CWS community, please email Veronica at</b> <a href=\"mailto:vesam@aol.com\">vesam@aol.com</a>.  We are creating a new page on our school website to highlight the interesting things CWS families do so that we can all support each others’ businesses.\n\n<b>November Dates:</b>\n\n1 November:  Masquerade Day\n\n5 November: Election Day-no school\n\n6 November: PTA Executive Board meeting after drop-off in library conference room\n\n8 November: SLT meeting-7:30am in Suma’s classroom\n\n11 November:  Veteran’s Day-no school\n\n<b>13 Novermber: PTA meeting after drop off in the lobby</b>--evening family conferences—no clubs\n\n14 November:  ½ day—11:30 dismissal--afternoon family conferences—no clubs\n\n22 November: -1/2 day for staff retreat-12:10 dismissal--Fancy Day—no clubs\n\n28 and 29 November-no school-Happy Thanksgiving!!!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>Upcoming:</b>\n\n4 Dec-PTA Executive Board meeting after drop off in library conference room\n\n12 Dec-pre-k non attendance day\n\n13 Dec:  Winter Craft Fair\n\n13 Dec-SLT meeting-7:30 in Suma’s classroom\n\n18 Dec-PTA meeting after drop off in lobby\n\nHoliday Break—21 December until 1 January-back to school 2 January 2014!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;','CWS Update for November 2013','','publish','open','open','','cws-update-for-november-2013','','','2013-11-07 12:40:44','2013-11-07 17:40:44','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1029',0,'post','',0),(890,1,'2013-07-01 10:03:10','2013-07-01 14:03:10','<strong>Thanks to Joyce, Rachel and Darryl for putting together the Fall clubs schedule--registration details will follow.  The first day of school is Weds 9 September.  Expect your child(ren) to receive a letter from their teacher at the end of August.  Any questions/concerns/ideas email </strong><a href=\"mailto:ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org\"><strong>ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org</strong></a><strong>.  Happy and safe summer to all!</strong>\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/fall-2013-after-school-clubs-schedule/cws-fall-13-clubs-2/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-897\">cws fall 13 clubs</a>','Fall 2013 After-School Clubs Schedule!','','publish','open','open','','fall-2013-after-school-clubs-schedule','','','2013-07-01 10:03:10','2013-07-01 14:03:10','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=890',0,'post','',0),(1081,1,'2013-12-12 22:28:41','2013-12-13 03:28:41','<strong><a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/cws-barnes-nobles-book-fair-code-11271582/print-6/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1082\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1082 alignleft\" alt=\"bookfair2013\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/CWSBNCODE2013.jpg\" width=\"400\" height=\"617\" /></a>Shop Barnes &amp; Noble this holiday season to raise money for new books for the school library. Use book fair voucher code #11271582 either online or at any Barnes &amp; Noble store and the library will receive back 20% of your purchases for new books. The voucher code is valid in any Barnes &amp; Noble store from December 13th-20th, and online from December 13th-25th. Please email to all of your friends and family as well as post on your social media pages. It is a great way to finish up the holiday shopping and support public schools and school libraries. </strong>','CWS Barnes & Noble\'s Book Fair CODE: 11271582','','publish','open','open','','cws-barnes-nobles-book-fair-code-11271582','','','2013-12-12 22:28:41','2013-12-13 03:28:41','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1081',0,'post','',0),(1086,1,'2013-12-20 11:55:13','2013-12-20 16:55:13','<table width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=\"center\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\">\n<table width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\">\n<table width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\">\n<table width=\"600\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<table width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\"></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<table border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=\"left\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"564\"><strong><strong>THANK YOU to Bari for running the Annual Winter Crafts Fair!! Many more thanks to the parents and community members who contributed their amazing talents in making this one of the most successful Winter Crafts Fair at CWS:  Keiko, Rosie, Sveta, Eric, Rachel, Alex, Anne, Cassy, Kim, Elizabeth, Joyce, Khadejah, Melissa, Sayoko, Roxanne, Judy, Jenny, Nancy, and Beth.</strong></strong>\n\nNY State Testing News: Thank you to our Advocacy Committee:  Julie, Jenny, Eric, Nancy, Kim, Kerri-Ann, Bryan and Hope for tirelessly educating themselves about this subject. They will be conducting information sessions in January for any parents who have questions about NY State Standardized Testing- please stay tuned for dates on these group Q&amp;A sessions.\n\n<strong><span style=\"font-family: tahoma\">SAVE THE DATE</span><span style=\"font-family: tahoma\">:The  Annual CWS MLK celebration will be Thursday, January 23rd!</span></strong>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: tahoma\">Seeking parent volunteers from ALL grades</span><span style=\"font-family: tahoma\">: kindergarteners have started eating lunch in their classrooms. We need volunteers to help out every day from 11-12. If you can volunteer, please talk to Joyce and leave a note for Elyssa and Beverly in the mailboxes in the office. Your help is greatly appreciated! </span></strong></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: tahoma\"> Raffles: Congrats to Rainie in Scott\'s class (again!)--she won 4 tickets to see The Big Apple Circus on New Year\'s Day--and congrats to Anne in Beverly\'s class (again!):  she won Saige, The American Girl Doll of the Year 2013!   The next raffle will be in January: win 2 tickets to see The New Victory Theater\'s production of Bob Marley\'s <em>Three Little Birds</em> on an available date of winner\'s choice in February.\n</span></strong></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">All classes have been working on<strong> Boxes of Hope with Project Hope</strong>, the organization run through Henry Street Settlement devoted to continued Hurricane Sandy recovery:  CWS children are exchanging letters and drawings with schoolchildren from  Rockaway and the North Jersey Shore. Thanks to Aurora, our school social worker, and Cristina from Project Hope for coordinating this program.</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: tahoma\">Happy Holidays to all!  See you on 2 January!  Coffee And... will resume 10 January.</span></strong></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n\n<em><strong>Families interested in The Children’s Workshop School, please email Joyce  (<a href=\"mailto:jborden@schools.nyc.gov\" target=\"_blank\">jborden@schools.nyc.gov</a>)or Dorothy (<a href=\"mailto:dcantwell2@schools.nyc.gov\" target=\"_blank\">dcantwell2@schools.nyc.gov</a>) to sign up for a  tour.  We look forward to meeting you!</strong></em>\n\n<em><strong>Upcoming  dates:  </strong></em>\n\n<em><strong>Mondays at 8:15am: 6 January, 2014; 27 January 2014; 10 February 2014; 24 February 2014</strong></em>\n\n<em><strong>Fridays at 9:00am:  10 January 2014; 24 January 2014; 7 February 2014 and 28 February 2014.</strong></em>\n\n</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"></div></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<table width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<table border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=\"left\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\"><a title=\"\" href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=d81bb01ac70c46a18b872cfe99903d02&amp;URL=http%3a%2f%2fchildrensworkshopschool.us5.list-manage.com%2ftrack%2fclick%3fu%3d22fb0e172fd6d94c84cac8bcd%26id%3d306541c4e8%26e%3d5594e39e5f\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/8.2.176.2/themes/base/clear.gif\" /> </a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"564\"></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\"></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>','Happy Holidays!  Back to School 2 January 2014','','publish','open','open','','happy-holidays-back-to-school-2-january-2014','','','2013-12-20 11:55:13','2013-12-20 16:55:13','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1086',0,'post','',0),(50,1,'2012-09-25 03:29:39','2012-09-25 03:29:39','','PTA Mixer 2012-2013 Flyer','Sep. 19, 1st PTA of the school year 2012-2013','inherit','open','open','','print','','','2012-09-25 03:29:39','2012-09-25 03:29:39','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/PTAMixer2012-13flyer.jpg',3,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(53,1,'2012-09-25 03:35:30','2012-09-25 03:35:30','','CWS Mixer + 1st PTA meeting of the school year 2012-2013','','inherit','open','open','','print-2','','','2012-09-25 03:35:30','2012-09-25 03:35:30','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/PTAMixer2012-13flyer1.jpg',2,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1047,1,'2013-11-16 15:32:47','2013-11-16 20:32:47','<p style=\"text-align: center\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1050\" alt=\"image001\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/image001-231x300.png\" width=\"231\" height=\"300\" /></p>\n<b>Project Hope Parent Workshop: Being Ready for an Emergency and Taking Care of Yourself--right after drop off on Weds 20 Nov in the lobby</b>--Project Hope is run through Henry Street Settlement and gives support to Hurricane Sandy survivors.  Thank you to Dorothy for bringing Project Hope to CWS.\n\n<b>CEC District 1 Meeting: Dual Language Programs—Weds 20 November at 6pm at PS20 on the corner of Houston and Essex Streets, childcare provided.</b> The DOE is interested in hearing from District 1 parents about <b>the possibility of creating a dual-language immersion Spanish middle school.</b> If you can attend, please rsvp (state childcare needs too) to <a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=311957c7bbbb4a53bbea831e8ec29162&amp;URL=mailto%3acec1%40schools.nyc.gov\">cec1@schools.nyc.gov</a> and please let the CWS PTA board know too <a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=311957c7bbbb4a53bbea831e8ec29162&amp;URL=mailto%3aptaeb%40childrensworkshopschool.org\">ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>.\n\n<b>Congrats to Anne in Beverly’s class—she won the Firebird Raffle</b>—2 tickets to see The Little Orchestra’s production of Firebird at New York City Center.  The beautiful puppets featured in the production are made by Teaching Artists  from <b>ArtsConnection, who will be running a puppet project at CWS in the spring</b>.  Details to follow!\n\n<strong>Rainbow Loom Raffle--2 chances to win: rainbow loom, a bunch of rubber bands and a carry case ($30 value)--$5 per chance--tix sold Friday 22 Nov during Coffee And... and drawing at Community Meeting. </strong>2 lucky winners will make rainbow loom bracelets all Happy Thanksgiving break long!\n\n<span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\';font-size: small\"><strong>SCRIPP GIFT CARDS!!--</strong>gift cards from various stores who donate a certain percentage of the gift card sale back to our school--<strong>please remember to submit your orders by 2 Dec</strong>---visit <strong>glscripp.com</strong> for a complete list of all the participating stores--for example:  Payless gives 13%; Land\'s End give 16%; Cinemark Theaters gives 15%.  Thanks to Tiffany and Marcia for coordinating the SCRIPP program.</span>\n\n<b>Artwork Sale at CWS Winter Craft Fair—Friday 13 December</b>\n\nFor this year\'s CWS Winter Craft Fair on Friday 13 December, we are going to experiment with adding an option to sell artwork.\n-Open to both adults and children.\n-Artwork must be presented framed, (IKEA will do) or on a matte, if on paper.\n-The artist does not need to be present at the sale.\n-The artist will list the price they wish to sell the piece for and the amount the school will receive if the piece is sold.\n-All work must be submitted to the office by Dec 9.\n\nPlease note:\n\nKeep the artwork size on the smaller side.\n\nIf a child submits a piece, please take into account that if it doesn\'t not sell they might be upset (or be prepared to buy their piece!)\n\nPlease contact : Bari Schlosser (Ezra\'s Mom -Miriam\'s 3rd grade class) <a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=311957c7bbbb4a53bbea831e8ec29162&amp;URL=mailto%3aBari161%40me.com\">Bari161@me.com</a>\n\nEric Slayton (Kai\'s Dad- Miriam\'s 3rd grade class) <a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=311957c7bbbb4a53bbea831e8ec29162&amp;URL=mailto%3aeric.slayton%40me.com\">eric.slayton@me.com</a>\n\n<b>ALSO—IF ANYONE HAS FOLDING TABLES, PLEASE EMAIL BARI at  bari161.me.com</b>\n\n<b>—WE NEED A BUNCH OF FOLDING TABLES FOR THE WINTER CRAFT FAIR!</b>\n\n<b> </b>','CWS Mid-November Update','','publish','open','open','','cws-mid-november-update','','','2013-11-16 15:32:47','2013-11-16 20:32:47','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1047',0,'post','',0),(62,1,'2012-09-25 03:51:24','2012-09-25 03:51:24','','CWSNewsLetter2011-2012 page1','','inherit','open','open','','cwsneswltr2012-1_page_1','','','2012-09-25 03:51:24','2012-09-25 03:51:24','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/CWSNeswLtr2012-1_Page_1.jpg',1,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(63,1,'2012-09-25 03:51:29','2012-09-25 03:51:29','','CWSNewsLetter2011-2012 page2','','inherit','open','open','','cwsneswltr2012-1_page_2','','','2012-09-25 03:51:29','2012-09-25 03:51:29','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/CWSNeswLtr2012-1_Page_2.jpg',2,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(906,1,'2013-08-02 11:44:37','2013-08-02 15:44:37','<strong>Thanks to Joyce for sharing these photos of our on-its-way-to-being-ready-for-the-first-day-of-school auditorium.  Thank you to the renovators for their hard work!</strong>\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/a-midsummer-nights-dream-almost-come-true-see-photos-of-our-renovated-auditorium/photo-1/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-907\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-907\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/photo-1-224x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"224\" height=\"300\" /></a><a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/a-midsummer-nights-dream-almost-come-true-see-photos-of-our-renovated-auditorium/photo-4/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-908\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-908\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/photo-4-224x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"224\" height=\"300\" /></a>','A Midsummer Night\'s Dream (Almost) Come True: See Photos of Our Renovated Auditorium','','publish','open','open','','a-midsummer-nights-dream-almost-come-true-see-photos-of-our-renovated-auditorium','','','2013-08-02 11:44:37','2013-08-02 15:44:37','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=906',0,'post','',1),(349,1,'2012-09-26 21:19:52','2012-09-26 21:19:52','<strong>PTA Meetings</strong> are usually held the third Wednesday of the month.\n<strong>SLT (School Leadership Team) Meetings</strong> are on the first Friday mornings of the month.\n<strong>CEC Meetings</strong> are held at P.S.20 on the second Wednesday of the month.\n\nPlease check monthly calendar for up-to-date dates and times.\n\n<strong>Dress-up Days-On the Last Friday</strong> of every month the 5th graders organize dress up days based on themes they have chosen. This is a fundraising opportunity to help the 5th Graders in their fundraising efforts for the annual Washington D.C. trip. Any CWS community member who would like to dress up is asked to donate $2 (all proceeds go to funding the Washington D.C. trip). Some typical dress up days include: Crazy Outfit Day, Pajama Day and Role Model Day. Look out for detailed dates on the calendar and help us get to Washington D.C.!\n\n<strong>Reading &amp; Writing Celebrations</strong> - When each class completes a writing/curriculum project the students\' families are invited to celebrate the students\' achievement as a classroom community. Parents and the administration are invited to read their stories, have some treats, and see first-hand the hard work and progress of the children. Dates TBA by teacher and class.','Monthly Events','','publish','open','open','','monthly-events','','','2012-09-26 21:19:52','2012-09-26 21:19:52','',344,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?page_id=349',0,'page','',0),(355,1,'2012-09-26 21:31:29','2012-09-26 21:31:29','<strong>Welcome Breakfast:</strong> For new and existing parents on the first days of school, to stay just a little bit longer after drop-off and mingle with other parents, get to know the PTA, the Parent Teacher Coordinator, sign up for committees, etc.\n\n<strong>CWS Mixer:</strong> An event where Children\'s Workshop School staff and parents of all CWS students can mingle, learn about things that go on at school.\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_50\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"233\"]<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/news-1/print/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-50\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-50\" title=\"PTA Mixer 2012-2013 Flyer\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/PTAMixer2012-13flyer-233x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"233\" height=\"300\" /></a> Sep. 19, 1st PTA of the school year 2012-2013[/caption]\n\n<strong>Harvest Festival: Fall 2012: Saturday, October 13, 2012 - </strong>A multi-cultural harvest celebration where all parents, students and staff of CWS are invited to bring food and activities from their culture for everyone to experience.\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/harvest-festival-this-coming-saturday-the-13th/print-5/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-525\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-525\" title=\"Harvest Festival 2012\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/cwsharvestfestival2012-229x300.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"229\" height=\"300\" /></a>\n\n<strong>Curriculum Nights: Fall 2012: Monday, September 24, 2012</strong> - In the fall, The Children\'s Workshop School staff invites the parents of all CWS students to come for an informative and exciting evening where they are able to learn about the curriculum their child will be exploring for the year. Curriculum also gives parents/guardians another change to visit their child\'s classroom and to be able to meet the various staff members their child will be learning with throughout the year.\n\n<strong>Family Conferences (Before winter break, and before Spring break) -</strong> We believe in the importance of conversing with parents/guardians about their child\'s progress. We also believe it is vital for the child to be involved in these discussions to allow them to be engaged with their own progress as a learner. As a result, students join their parents/ guardians and teachers in November and April for Family Conferences.\n\n<a title=\"Winter Crafts Fair\" href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/community/annual-events/winter-crafts-fair/\"><strong>The Winter Crafts Fair</strong> </a> <strong>Friday, December 7, 2012</strong> - A pop-up shop hosted by parents at the school lobby in the beginning of December to kick-off the holiday shopping. A percentage of the sales at the holiday craft fair goes to the CWS PTA to fund programs necessary for the school.\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/11302011-cws-holiday-crafts-fair-is-coming-up-dont-miss-it/cwscraftfairposter2011/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-87\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-87\" title=\"CWScraftfairposter2011\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/CWScraftfairposter2011-220x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"220\" height=\"300\" /></a>\n\n<strong>The Book Fair</strong> - The Children\'s Workshop school is very happy to partner with the Union Square Barnes and Noble to have an annual book fair, which is held before Winter Break. The book fair lasts several days, allowing each class to take a quick trip to Barnes and Noble to purchase books as well as allowing for a wonderful Saturday Book Fair CWS event at the store. On a Saturday during the book fair local authors and CWS teachers come and read on the children\'s storytelling stage at Barnes and Nobles for CWS families. Proceeds The Children\'s Workshop School earns from the fair go to maintaining our beautiful library. Purchase code is: 10613180\n\n<strong><a title=\"Die Telemänner in CWS\" href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/community/annual-events/die-telemanner-in-cws/\">Die Telemanner</a> -</strong> A cultural exchange program with the Die Telemanner Baroque Youth Orchestra from Stuttgart, Germany - Free Concert at Turtle Bay Music School (Friday, Jan. 7 2012) and Children\'s concert/reception at CWS on Saturday, January 8, 2012.\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?attachment_id=92\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-92\" title=\"german_orchestra\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/german_orchestra.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"268\" height=\"197\" /></a>\n\n<strong>Honoring the Dream -</strong> All School Performance (January 14, 2012) - This annual, all-school performance celebrates the vision and dream of Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr and reaffirms our hope for a just and peaceful world. Teachers work with the students to develop class performances and every child has the opportunity to be a part of the presentation. We have the Honoring the Dream Celebration off-site to accommodate our growing community. It is a moving and exhilarating experience and is open to the public.\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/community/annual-events/drmartinlutherkingjrphoto_1/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-671\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-671\" title=\"drmartinlutherkingjrphoto_1\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/drmartinlutherkingjrphoto_1-300x225.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a>\n\n<strong>All School Ice Skating (End of January-February) -</strong> The Children\'s Workshop School comes together as a whole school for a wonderful time ice skating as a community. Families are also welcome to join the fun. This past year we skated at Lasker Rink in Central Park amidst a beautiful snowfall!\n\n<strong>Schoolapalooza -</strong> Start lining up a babysitter.. and inviting friends...to the best parents\' (and teachers’) night out of the school year, featuring fabulous refreshments, marvelous music (last year was Lisa Lisa) and the most Spectacular Silent Auction, all to support CWS.\nMore information on this year’s Schoolapalooza TBA. Please check back with us again!\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/312012-spread-the-word-for-schoolapalooza-2012-coming-up-march-30/cws_schoolapa2012/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-86\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-86\" title=\"CWS_Schoolapa2012\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/CWS_Schoolapa2012-194x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"194\" height=\"300\" /></a>\n\n<strong>The Annual Arts and Science Fair, Saturday, May 11, 2013 -</strong> The Annual Arts and Science Fair! Held in May in our School Yard and building, the Arts &amp;Science Fair is fun for the entire family… fantastic food, music, arts and crafts including GLOP, Tie Dye, Face Painting to name a few, games, performances, raffles, rummage sale and more. Contact Judy at<a href=\"mailto: judy@childrensworkshopschool.org\"> judy@childrensworkshopschool.org</a> to volunteer.\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/512012-cws-arts-science-fair-saturday-may-12-11am-3pm/print-3/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-90\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-90\" title=\"Arts &amp; Science Fair Flyer\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/CWSscience+artfairPOSTER2012-231x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"231\" height=\"300\" /></a>\n\n<strong>All School Family Picnic (June, 2013) -</strong> In June The Children\'s Workshop School community has an all school family picnic. Students, families and CWS staff enjoy the day of fun!\n\n<strong>CWS Band Concert (June, 2013) -</strong> Fourth and fifth graders at The Children\'s Workshop School are fortunate enough to have the opportunity to join the school band. The students practice twice a week and put on band concerts throughout the year. Students who participated in the band have gone on to continue playing music in middle, high school and college and have received music scholarships!\n\n<strong>Annual CWS Talent Show (May, 2013)</strong> - Third, fourth and fifth graders participate in an annual talent show in June. The show includes any 3rd – 5th grader that is interested in showcasing a talent they have. The opening and closing all talent show numbers are chosen and choreographed by the after school Talent Show Club and the fifth graders perform their own number as the graduating class. From telling jokes, to singing, to a puppet show, our talent show represents the individuality and creativity of our students.\n\nPoetry All Over Celebration\n\n...and more!\nCheck the calendar and backpacks for updates.','Annual Events','','publish','open','open','','annual-events','','','2012-09-26 21:31:29','2012-09-26 21:31:29','',344,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?page_id=355',0,'page','',0),(67,1,'2012-09-25 04:00:42','2012-09-25 04:00:42','','Haagen Dazs!','','inherit','open','open','','picture-30','','','2012-09-25 04:00:42','2012-09-25 04:00:42','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/Picture-30.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(82,1,'2012-09-25 04:13:58','2012-09-25 04:13:58','','CWS_chico1','','inherit','open','open','','cws_chico1','','','2012-09-25 04:13:58','2012-09-25 04:13:58','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/CWS_chico1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(83,1,'2012-09-25 04:14:00','2012-09-25 04:14:00','','CWS_chico2','','inherit','open','open','','cws_chico2','','','2012-09-25 04:14:00','2012-09-25 04:14:00','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/CWS_chico2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(84,1,'2012-09-25 04:14:01','2012-09-25 04:14:01','','CWS_chico3','','inherit','open','open','','cws_chico3','','','2012-09-25 04:14:01','2012-09-25 04:14:01','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/CWS_chico3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(85,1,'2012-09-25 04:14:03','2012-09-25 04:14:03','','CWS_chico4','','inherit','open','open','','cws_chico4','','','2012-09-25 04:14:03','2012-09-25 04:14:03','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uplo