Win 4 tickets to see The Big Apple Circus at Lincoln Center on New Year\'s Day!  $2 per chance/3 chances for $5 -</strong>-tickets sold during Coffee And.. on 6 December, 13 December and 20 December-with the <strong>drawing at Community Meeting on 20 December.</strong>\n\n<strong>Thank you to New York Theatre Ballet and Big Apple Circus for their generous donations of the tickets.</strong>\n\n<strong>Congrats to Liany and Redding</strong>--they each won a rainbow loom with carrying case and extra rubber bands!\n\n<strong>Thanks to all families who participate in our fundraising efforts</strong> by helping out, or taking a chance with our raffles or buying  books, and Coffee And... before Friday Community Meetings.  <strong>All proceeds go to funding enrichment programs for all CWS students</strong>--everything  from Turtle Bay Music School to the CWS Band to Bent on Learning Yoga.\n\n<strong>Penny Harvest!</strong>--Support Penny Harvest at CWS--send change (bills welcome too) in to school with your child.  Every week, our Penny Harvest leaders from Elyssa and Michelle\'s class and Crystal\'s class will go around to each classroom, collecting all the change.  Our Penny Harvest collection will go to a charity still to be decided.\n\n<strong>Happy Thanksgiving to All!</strong>','Winter Craft Fair-Fri 13 Dec and December Raffles:  Nutcracker and Big Apple Circus','','publish','open','open','','winter-craft-fair-fri-13-dec-and-december-raffles-nutcracker-and-big-apple-circus','','','2013-11-27 14:04:44','2013-11-27 19:04:44','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1058',0,'post','',0),(301,1,'2012-09-25 15:43:34','2012-09-25 15:43:34','','toystory','','inherit','open','open','','toystory','','','2012-09-25 15:43:34','2012-09-25 15:43:34','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/toystory.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(900,1,'2013-07-10 08:16:20','2013-07-10 12:16:20','<p align=\"center\"><strong>The Children’s Workshop School Update</strong></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>For Summer 2013</strong></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://www.childrensworkshopschool.org/\">http://www.childrensworkshopschool.org</a></p>\n<p align=\"center\">212-414-9531 or <a href=\"mailto:ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org\">ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org</a></p>\n<p align=\"center\">”We’re all a family under one sky!”</p>\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Thank you to Rossella, Pierluigi, Ciara and Ilaria, Gianlucca and the staff of Gnocco for hosting Maria’s 20<sup>th</sup> Anniversary Celebration on 20 June-and thanks to Rosie for making the poster!</strong>  Over 100 teachers, administrators, parents, children, alumni, former teachers, and alumni parents gathered to celebrate and hear Maria’s co-founder Jean speak about the early days of CWS.  Gary presented Maria with the giant 20, made by Andrew and signed by all students, teachers and staff.  The kids serenaded Maria with “We’re All a Family Under One Sky” and “Black Socks.”  Maria was surprised and delighted!\n\nCongrats to our fifth graders on their <strong>Moving Up Ceremony</strong>!    <strong>Thank you to Bess, her mom Lisa and Elizabeth for making and sharing the inspiring film “Raise Your Voice.”</strong>  Bess was so affected by the 5th grade study of the Civil Rights Movement that she wanted to make a short film in which her classmates would each choose a word and sentence that represented what the Civil Rights Movement meant to them.  <strong>Thank you to Jessica for creating the yearbook, a great memento featuring each graduate.  Thanks to Joyce, Luis and the fourth grade families for hosting the luncheon afterwards; much thanks to Beverly and her husband Dee for decorating and providing the space for the celebration and to PS34 for lending us their auditorium.</strong>\n\n<strong>Congrats to all the performers in the 3/4/5 Grade Talent Show and thanks to Jessica and Crystal, as always, for organizing and directing. </strong>Everyone enjoyed the show!  Performances ranged from Double Dutch wizardry to the Abbott and Costello routine “Who’s on First?” to songs like “Girls Just Wanna Have Fun” to violin and guitar solos.  Congrats to all the performers!\n\nThank you to Jia Lee, parent and teacher at The Earth School, for meeting with us about the growing concern over high-stakes testing (DOE-mandated K-2 testing is on the horizon).  Julie will post information and resources to our website before school starts in September.  In the meantime, go to <strong>changethestakes.org</strong> for more information.\n\nThank you to Gary, Elizabeth, Tiffany and Judy for coordinating and putting together the <strong>CD of Community Meeting Songs</strong> and to Mario for Tu Casa studios for donating his studio space.  Each class is featured singing their favorite song:  everything from Jaina’s class singing “This Land is Your Land” to Scott’s class singing “When the Rain Comes Down.<strong>”  We will be selling the CDs as soon as school starts for $20 each and will raffle off a CD (almost) every Friday at Community Meeting ($1 per chance).</strong>\n\nThanks to <strong>Chico,</strong> the iconic LES muralist, for coming in to touch up the Under the Sea mural he painted for CWS on the third floor.\n\nWe did not have a<strong> Field Day</strong> this year—Bill, the adaptive physical education teacher, has always been the one to organize it but he was not assigned to our school.  Next year, we will see to it that we have a Field Day, whether we are lucky enough to have Bill or not!\n\nDorothy and Maria have met with Selim Ozalp, the architect who designed our library and he will re-work the space to create a <strong>memorial area for Carol</strong>, our recently-retired librarian who passed away in the Spring and is greatly missed.\n\n<strong>We will have composting of school lunch food scraps starting in the Fall, thanks to Leslie and the Nutrition Committee.</strong>  The compost buckets, once full, will be dumped and buried in The Children’s Garden on the corner of 12<sup>th</sup> and B by our students. CWS  is piloting the program; if all goes as it should, EVCS and The Spectrum School will also compost school lunch in the Spring.\n\n<strong>Thanks to Rina, The Children’s Workshop School is a participant in </strong><strong><em>Schoola Stitch’s Children’s Clothing Drive</em></strong><em>. </em><strong>Your clothing donations benefit our school.  Go to <a href=\"http://www.schoola.com/labs\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.schoola.com/labs</a></strong><strong> to sign up, select Children’s Workshop and request a bag. You will be mailed a postage-paid collection bag which you then fill with gently-used name brand children’s clothing. UPS picks it up free of charge.  Once Schoola Stitch receives the clothing, they sort it, sell it and give up to 40% of the proceeds to our school. On average they are seeing between $30-$50 per bag of clothes donated back to participating schools.  </strong>\n\nThe New York Public Library\'s Main Branch at 42<sup>nd</sup> and 5<sup>th</sup> Ave has a great can’t-miss hands-on exhibit<strong>, The ABC of It:  Why Children’s Books Matter </strong>on view til March 2014.<strong></strong>\n\n<strong>Maria recommends a weekend day trip to Governor’s Island—take the free ferry and explore!  <a href=\"http://www.govisland.com/html/home/home.shtml\">http://www.govisland.com/html/home/home.shtml</a></strong>\n\nIf your child(ren) did not receive a <strong>Summer Reading Journal</strong> from our Barnes and Noble Book Fair (which benefitted our lovely library), download it here: <a href=\"http://img1.imagesbn.com/pimages/kids/summerreading/2013/bnsummertearpad.pdf\">http://img1.imagesbn.com/pimages/kids/summerreading/2013/bnsummertearpad.pdf</a>  When your child reads 8 books, s/he will receive a free book at Barnes and Noble.\n\nHappy and safe summer to all!  <strong>The public pools offer free swimming lessons and give out free breakfast and lunch.</strong>  Text NYCMeals to 877-877 for a full list of breakfast/lunch sites.\n\n<strong>See you on 9 September-and the auditorium should/will be finished!</strong>   Any questions/concerns/ideas please email <a href=\"mailto:ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org\">ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>. Teachers will send out their letters at the end of August!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;','CWS Summer 2013 Update','','publish','open','open','','cws-summer-2013-update','','','2013-07-10 08:16:20','2013-07-10 12:16:20','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=900',0,'post','',0),(326,1,'2012-09-26 19:37:10','2012-09-26 19:37:10','Weekly Updates Sept 26 2012','Weekly Update 9262012','','inherit','open','open','','childrens-workshop-school-weekly-update-9262012','','','2012-09-26 19:37:10','2012-09-26 19:37:10','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/Childrens-Workshop-School-Weekly-Update-9262012.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(1092,1,'2014-01-04 15:21:51','2014-01-04 20:21:51','&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Welcome back to school!</strong>\n\n<strong>Coffee And...Book Sale will resume on Fri 10 January</strong> before Community Meeting, along with the Lego Minecraft Raffle.  Thanks, as always, to Melissa, Natalie, Roxanne, Sayoko, Paul and all those who contribute and consume.\n\n<strong>Saturday 11 January 9:30-3:30—workshop hosted by CEC-1 at the Lower East Side Girls Club with community leaders about District 1 schools, particularly the new school in the works in the Seward Park Urban Renewal Area.</strong> Please see more info on the Community Education Council-District 1 website:  <a href=\"http://cecd1.org/2013/12/10/372/\">http://cecd1.org/2013/12/10/372/</a>\n<h3>THANK YOU to Darryl (Justine and Jane\'s mom), our Mural and Painting Clubs\' teaching artist, for arranging an exhibit of the clubs\' artists at Michael Mut Project Space!\nThe How Do I Love Me? art show will run from January 11th-24th, 2014. Opening reception will be Saturday, January 11th, 4pm-6pm, 97 Avenue C.</h3>\n<strong>Thursday 23 January at 6pm is our All-School Martin Luther King Living the Dream Celebration in the huge auditorium at ICE on 15th Street between 1st and 2nd Avenues!  </strong>Each class will perform, as well as Patrizia\'s Improvisational  Dance Club and Mr. Scott\'s Experimental Dance Group.  This is a beautiful annual event, celebrating 20 years of The Children\'s Workshop School community\'s commitment to Martin\'s vision of peace and social justice.  Thank you in advance to our teachers, Maria, Dorothy, Joyce and our children for their hard work putting on a great show!\n\n<strong>Raffle!:  Win 2 tickets to see<em> Bob Marley\'s Three Little Birds </em>at The New Victory Theater</strong> on an available date in February of the winner\'s choice. Perfect for ages 5 and up.  Tickets sold during Coffee And...Book Sale on Fri 24 January and Fri 31 January, with drawing at Community Meeting on 31 January.  Thank you to the New Victory Theater for their generous donation of the tickets.\n\n<strong>Other Important Dates in January:</strong>\n\nWeds 8 January--PTA Executive Board meeting after drop-off in library conference room\n\nFri 10 January-School Leadership Team meeting in Suma\'s classroom at 7:30am\n\n<strong>Weds 15 January-PTA General Meeting in the lobby after drop-off</strong>\n\n<strong>Friday 17 January--1/2 day</strong> for teacher professional development--dismissal date tba\n\n<strong>Monday 20 January-Martin Luther King Day-no school</strong>\n\n<strong><em>Upcoming Important Dates in February:</em></strong>\n\nWeds 5 Feb:  PTA Executive Board meeting after drop-off in library conference room\n\n<strong>Sat 8 Feb and Sun 9 Feb:  Barnes and Noble Book Fair to benefit our lovely library!  Thanks to Nicole for organizing.</strong>\n\n<strong>Weds 12 Feb--PTA General Meeting--6pm in the lobby--pizza and childcare provided</strong>\n\nWinter Break!:  17-21 February--No School--enjoy!  Back to school on Monday 24 February.\n\n<em><strong>School Tours:  Families interested in The Children’s Workshop School, please email Joyce  (<a href=\"mailto:jborden@schools.nyc.gov\" target=\"_blank\">jborden@schools.nyc.gov</a>)or Dorothy (<a href=\"mailto:dcantwell2@schools.nyc.gov\" target=\"_blank\">dcantwell2@schools.nyc.gov</a>) to sign up for a  tour.  We look forward to meeting you!</strong></em>\n\n<em><strong>Upcoming  dates:  </strong></em>\n\n<em><strong>Mondays at 8:15am: 6 January, 2014; 27 January 2014; 10 February 2014; 24 February 2014</strong></em>\n\n<em><strong>Fridays at 9:00am:  10 January 2014; 24 January 2014; 7 February 2014 and 28 February 2014.</strong></em>\n\n&nbsp;','Happy New Year!','','publish','open','open','','happy-new-year','','','2014-01-04 15:21:51','2014-01-04 20:21:51','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1092',0,'post','',0),(1105,1,'2014-01-22 13:52:02','2014-01-22 18:52:02','Hello CWS Families,\n\n&nbsp;\n\nDue to the extremely cold temperatures predicted for the evening on Thursday, January 23<sup>rd</sup>, we have decided to cancel our MLK Honoring the Dream celebration.  Making this decision was not an easy one, and it is only the second time in twenty years that we have had to do this, however, the safety and well being of the children, families and staff at our school always comes first.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nWe have also taken into consideration the difficulty that some families would face in having to bring children out on such a cold and blustery night.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nNever fear – the show will go on! In the coming weeks, we will have presentations of the classes’ MLK performance during Community Meetings.  The schedule of performances is below, we hope you are able to join us as we continue to celebrate Dr. King’s Dream!\n\n&nbsp;\n\nPeace,\n\n&nbsp;\n\nMaria\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>January 31<sup>st</sup></b> –  PreK and K Classes\n\n<b>February 7<sup>th</sup></b> – 1/2 Classes\n\n<b>February 14<sup>th</sup></b> – 3<sup>rd</sup> Grade Classes\n\n<b>February 28<sup>th</sup></b> – 4<sup>th</sup> Grade Classes\n\n<b>March 7<sup>th</sup></b> – 3<sup>rd</sup>/4<sup>th</sup>/5<sup>th</sup> Grade Class and 5<sup>th</sup> Grade Classes\n\n&nbsp;','','','publish','open','open','','1105','','','2014-01-22 13:52:02','2014-01-22 18:52:02','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1105',0,'post','',0),(1109,1,'2014-01-23 15:06:22','2014-01-23 20:06:22','<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: #000000;font-family: Tahoma;font-size: small\"><strong>Spring Clubs!-</strong>-Thanks to Joyce and Rachel for putting together a great selection of clubs--the listing went home in backpacks.  All the favorites, from Hip Hop to Mural Club to Robotics to Sports Club return, as well as some new clubs: Knitting, Rainbow Loom, Jewelry Making.  Registration is Tues 28 Jan and Weds 29 Jan in the lobby from 7:45-9:00.  Fall Clubs end 7 Feb and Spring Clubs run 10 Feb til 20 June.</span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\"><strong>Phone Drive-</strong>-Thanks to Paul, Elizabeth, Tiffany, John, Kevin, Lara, Steve, Maria and Hope for running the phone drive on Mon 27 Jan and Tues 28 Jan in the evening.</span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\"><strong>Save the dates!--Saturday 8 February and Sunday 9 February--the CWS Library Book Fair at Barnes and Noble Union Square. </strong> Thanks to Nicole, we have a great line-up of readings:  Victoria Kann, former CWS mom, reading from her latest <em>Emeraldlicious </em>on 9 Feb at 11:30; Madeline Valentine reading her book <em>The Bad Birthday Idea</em> at noon on 8 Feb and many more.</span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\">Evening PTA Meeting--Weds 12 February at 6pm in the lobby--childcare provided, thanks to Joyce and Sonia!</span></strong></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><strong> </strong></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\">FUN STUFF TO DO:</span></strong></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\"><strong>Central Park Winter Jam!-</strong>-Saturday 25 jan from 11-3--FREE---cross-country skiing, snowshoeing, learn to ski and snowboard.  Check out <a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=3eeeb8b3c43b4cca8cac07816642a4a2&amp;URL=http%3a%2f%2fwww.nyc.gov%2fparks%2fwinterjam\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.nyc.gov/parks/winterjam</a></span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\"><strong>New York Theatre Ballet\'s production of The Alice in Wonderland Follies</strong> at Florence Gould Hall on Saturday 25 Jan at 1:00 or Sunday 26 jan at 11:00, 1:00 or 3:30. 1 hour long-perfect for ages 3-10.  Check out:  <a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=3eeeb8b3c43b4cca8cac07816642a4a2&amp;URL=http%3a%2f%2fwww.nytb.org\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.nytb.org</a></span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\"><strong>New exhibit at The Morgan Library--The Little Prince:  A New York Story--24 Jan-27 Apri</strong>l.  See original drawings and manuscript drafts of Saint-Exupery\'s beloved classic, written while he lived in NYC.</span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\"><a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=3eeeb8b3c43b4cca8cac07816642a4a2&amp;URL=http%3a%2f%2fwww.themorgan.org%2fexhibitions%2fexhibition.asp%3fid%3d90\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.themorgan.org/exhibitions/exhibition.asp?id=90</a></span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\"><strong>Ongoing at the New York Public Library main branch at 5th Ave and 42nd Street until 23 March:  The ABC of It:  Why Children\'s Books Matter-</strong>-featuring favorites like Goodnight Moon, Alice in Wonderland and A Wrinkle in Time</span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=3eeeb8b3c43b4cca8cac07816642a4a2&amp;URL=http%3a%2f%2fwww.nypl.org%2fevents%2fexhibitions%2fabc-it\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.nypl.org/events/exhibitions/abc-it</a></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Chinese Lunar New Year Parade!</strong>--<strong>Celebrate the Year of the Horse!--Sunday 2 February at 1pm-parade starts on Mott and Hester Streets.</strong></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\"><strong>Thunderbird Native American Dancers Annual Concert and Pow-Wow at The Theater for the New City, 155 First Avenue--31 January til 9 Feburary.</strong>  Childrens\' matinees on Saturday and Sunday at 3:00</span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=3eeeb8b3c43b4cca8cac07816642a4a2&amp;URL=http%3a%2f%2fwww.theaterforthenewcity.net%2fthunder.htm\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.theaterforthenewcity.net/thunder.htm</a></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><em><strong>School Tours:  Families interested in The Children’s Workshop School, please email Joyce  (<a href=\"mailto:jborden@schools.nyc.gov\" target=\"_blank\">jborden@schools.nyc.gov</a>)or Dorothy (<a href=\"mailto:dcantwell2@schools.nyc.gov\" target=\"_blank\">dcantwell2@schools.nyc.gov</a>) to sign up for a  tour.  We look forward to meeting you!</strong></em></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"></div>','Spring Clubs and Book Fair','','publish','open','open','','spring-clubs-and-book-fair','','','2014-01-23 15:06:22','2014-01-23 20:06:22','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1109',0,'post','',0),(1116,1,'2014-01-24 16:07:42','2014-01-24 21:07:42','Since the MLK Celebration was cancelled, today\'s community meeting was a glimps of the children singing all together. It was the first time all grades sang together on the stage. They were super energetic! Happy Singing! (ps. excuse the bad quality of the video. but you can get the idea!) <a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/2014-01-24-09.16.43.mov\">&lt;&lt;&lt;VIDEO LINK HERE&gt;&gt;&gt;</a>','Practicing the MLK celebration all-school-songs','','publish','open','open','','practicing-the-mlk-celebration-all-school-songs','','','2014-01-24 16:07:42','2014-01-24 21:07:42','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1116',0,'post','',0),(1127,1,'2014-01-27 21:35:32','2014-01-28 02:35:32','<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/spring-clubs-2014.pdf\">CLICK HERE &gt;&gt;&gt; FOR Spring clubs 2014 BROCHURE</a>\n\nDear Parents,\nWelcome to a new session of after school clubs! Please take time to read this letter and the clubs list, as there is some new information.\nSPRING SESSION REGISTRATION DATES: TUESDAY, JANUARY 28th &amp; WEDNESDAY, JANUARY 29th. REGISTRATION WILL BE HELD IN THE LOBBY FROM 7:45AM TO 9:00am ON BOTH DAYS. Spring clubs will begin on Monday, February 10th and end June 20th, 2014.\n\nTHERE WILL BE NO BREAK IN BETWEEN FALL AND SPRING CLUBS.\n\nRemember: In order to cover the club\'s expenses, each club MUST have a minimum of 7 children in order for the club to run. Once again, PLEASE FILL OUT ALL NECESSARY FORMS BEFORE COMING TO REGISTRATION. THIS IS EXTREMELY IMPORTANT! This will help the registration process move more quickly.This year, we will add an extra week onto each semester of clubs making each club last 19 weeks instead of 17 as in the past, in order to offer clubs earlier in Mid-September and later in June to accommodate busy parents. Because of that and increasing costs, all clubs will cost $260 for the 19 sessions which makes the cost for each session $13.70. Some clubs require a $10 or $20 materials fee. We will offer a 20% discount to those enrolling in 4 or more clubs.\n\nMAKE CHECKS PAYABLE TO THE CWS PTA. WE ACCEPT CREDIT CARDS AS WELL. DO NOT HAND IN REGISTRATION FORMS TO THE OFFICE! There will be a lottery for clubs that are over enrolled so there is no need to worry about being first at registration. Parents may register for the children of ONE other family in addition to their own. So, if you are unable to make registration for whatever reason, you may ask another parent to register your children for you. A list of the clubs will be displayed at registration so parents will be able to see which clubs are full and which have spaces left.\n\nAs ever, no one should hesitate to join a club for lack of money. If your family needs assistance, contact me or Maria Velez-Clarke. If you have any questions or concerns, you may contact Joyce in the office.\n\nSnack will be provided to all children right after school. Parents or caretakers should pick up their children promptly at 4:45 in the lobby. Please be on time! Club leaders have to leave promptly at 4:45. You also have the option of putting your child in the <a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/EXTENDED-LETTER-FALL-2012.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">extended day option</a> and pick your child up any time between 4:45 and 5:50pm. Clubs do not meet on half days, school holidays, and parent teacher conference days.<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/EXTENDED-LETTER-FALL-2012.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"> (Click here for detailed pricing for Extended Day&gt;&gt;).</a>\n\nWe are also very pleased to announce that our school secretary, Joyce Borden, and Rachael Frank, a CWS parent will be helping again with the clubs program this year. Many programs are also taught by the CWS teachers and parents. Thank you so much for all the support!\n\nFor alternative options for School Holidays, Green Apple Kids Holiday camp is held at Earth School (Avenue B and 6th Street)  from 8am - 4pm. For more information, please click &gt;&gt;&gt; <a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/community/afterschool-clubs/gak_brochure_3rd_draft-docx/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-943\">Green Apple Kids Brochure 2013-2014</a> and <a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/community/afterschool-clubs/green-apple-kids-mini-camp-application-docx/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-944\">Green Apple Kids Mini Camp Application</a>.\n\nDays of the Green Apple Kids Holiday Camp (23 Days in all)\n\nOctober 14- Columbus Day\n\nNovember 5- Election Day\n\nNovember 11- Veterans Day\n\nNovember 29- Day after Thanksgiving\n\nDecember 23,24,26,27,30,31- Winter Recess\n\nJanuary 20- Martin Luther King Day\n\nFebruary 17,18,19,20,21- Mid Winter Recess\n\nApril 14,15,16,17,18,21,22- Spring Break\n\n&nbsp;','CLUBS REGISTRATION TUESDAY & WEDNESDAY, JANUARY 28 & 29 in the morning!','','publish','open','open','','1127','','','2014-01-27 21:35:32','2014-01-28 02:35:32','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1127',0,'post','',0),(382,1,'2012-09-26 22:06:45','2012-09-26 22:06:45','','favicon','','inherit','open','open','','favicon','','','2012-09-26 22:06:45','2012-09-26 22:06:45','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/favicon.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1216,1,'2014-04-16 09:09:16','2014-04-16 13:09:16','<img class=\"size-full wp-image-1215 alignleft\" alt=\"Schoola_call_2014_8-200x300\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Schoola_call_2014_8-200x300.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" />\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1228\" alt=\"artsandsciencefair2014\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/artsandsciencefair2014-230x300.jpg\" width=\"230\" height=\"300\" />\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.seedsofchangegrant.com/uploads/fce15adf-92ec-4e03-a361-9f0438c90c57.jpg\" />\n\n<span style=\"color: #0000ff\"><strong>Thanks to all members of the CWS community who have donated auction items for Schoolapalooza-30 May at the Clemente Soto Velez Center!  We will have a solicitation day on Fri 2 May--email Tiffany or Rachel if you would like to join a group of parents canvassing the East Village and Williamsburg for restaurant and hotel donations:  zergestiffany@gmail or rachiefrank505@yahoo.com.  See the Schoolapalooza website for the donation letter and auction forms:  http://www.schoola.org</strong></span>\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">Saturday 10 May:  The 20th Annual Art and Science Fair!  Email Judy to help out: garnar-wortzel@att.net.  Make food, do facepainting, run a science project table, help in the kitchen, donate handmedowns for the rummage sale.</span></strong>\n<p align=\"center\"><b><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\">NEW</span></b><b> Parent Survey</b></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><b>This is <span style=\"text-decoration: underline\">NOT</span> the School Environment Survey (Green Envelopes)</b></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><b>That Was Given Out at School.</b></p>\n<p align=\"center\"> <b>Please Click on The Link to Complete This Short Survey</b></p>\n\n<h3 align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://twitter.us3.list-manage.com/track/click?u=099dfdaae98198ad83b0be7ba&amp;id=6fae82520b&amp;e=296833d790\" target=\"_blank\">https://survey.vovici.com/se.ashx?s=705E3ED0020246C1</a></h3>\n<h3 align=\"center\"> <b><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\">The Deadline to Complete this Survey isMay 1st</span></b></h3>\n<p align=\"center\"> <b>The NYC Department of Education seeks feedback to keep parents better informed about school quality. The DOE currently provides school quality information to parents through two main sources: the Progress Report and the Quality Review. The DOE is considering integrating this information with other sources to provide a better, more accurate picture of school quality to parents. </b><b>Your responses to the questions will help the DOE determine the best way to integrate and communicate this information in the future.  </b></p>\n<strong><span style=\"color: #008000\">Please take time to vote-daily!-for the Campos Children\'s Garden next door to school to get a Seeds of Change grant (see photo above--CWS got a grant last year to revitalize the garden after Hurricane Sandy and this grant will continue the work)-voting ends 21 April:</span></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #008000\">https://www.seedsofchangegrant.com/TheGallery.aspx?id=419692ac-246f-4219-97a6-b69f476e5261</span></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #000000\">Turtle Bay Music School\'s Saturday Music Project is now accepting applications for next school year 14/15:</span></strong>  Rising 3rd, 4th and 5th graders are encouraged to apply--free instrument instruction and music program on Saturdays.  Deadline is 7 June:\n\nhttp://www.tbms.org/saturday-music-project/\n\n<strong>National Children\'s Chorus audition<span style=\"color: #000000\">s</span></strong>--Thurs 1 May at Church of St Paul the Apostle by Columbus Circle, ages 5-16:  nationalchildrenschorus.com\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">S</span><span style=\"color: #ff0000\"><strong>c</strong>hools are Us:  Who Makes Decisions in Our Public Schools? is a flow chart created by the Center for Urban Pedagogy that explains the complicated  NYC public education system:  welcometocup.org</span></strong>\n\n<span style=\"color: #800080\"><strong>Raffle!:  Win 2 tickets to see The Little Orchestra Society\'s production of Lemony Snickett\'s <em>The Composer is Dead</em> </strong></span>at Lincoln Center on Saturday 17 May at 11am.  $2 per chance/2 chances for $5.  Tickets on sale before Community Meeting on 2 May and 9 May-drawing 9 May at Community Meeting.\n\nLooking forward to the Fall--Mark your Calendars Now!:  <span style=\"color: #0000ff\"><strong>The Anna Howard Shaw School Building Centennial Celebration will be on Saturday 20 September</strong></span>--all 3 schools in our building (CWS, EVCS, PS94-The Spectrum School) will join together for a family-fun day to celebrate the 100th birthday of our school building!  To get involved, email ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #008000\">Esther\'s Half-Day Camp Club: karate, yoga, art projects on half- days--16 May, 3 June, 9 June--talk to Joyce to sign up.</span></strong>\n\n23 April--Community Education Council for District 1 meeting with special presentation on Special Education and IEPs--6pm at NEST+M dinner and childcare provided\n\n24 April--8am in lobby:  The Advocacy Committee will lead a discussion about the state tests\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n\n<strong>3 May--Free Block Party and Birthday Cake Contest at Henry Street Settlement\n</strong>\n\nHenry Street is hosting a FREE block party to celebrate the 147th birthday of our founder, Lillian Wald, on <strong>Saturday, May 3, 2014</strong>, as part of Lower East Side History Month.\n\nThe party will be held at 265 Henry Street from noon to 3 p.m.\n\nActivities include a cake contest,* refreshments, music and dancing, arts activities for children, face-painting, blood pressure screenings, tours of the historic settlement house and more.\n\n</div>\n6 May-after drop-off at The Neighborhood School 121 East 3rd St:  Diversity Discussion--meeting to create a diversity policy to present to Chancellor Farina\n\n10 May--Art and Science Fair\n\n16 May: half day-12:10 pick up.  Bent on Learning and The Shala Yoga Studio will be honored at Community Meeting for bringing yoga to CWS kids\n\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000\">21 May:  PTA meeting at 6pm in lobby</span>\n\n24 May:  The Experimental Dance Group (EDG) will perform at The Theater for the New City at 2pm\n\n26 May--no school--Memorial Day--Hello Summer!\n\n30 May:  Schoolapalooza-- Lisa Lisa will perform!','20th Annual Art and Science Fair 10 May!  Schoolapalooza 30 May! and more...','','publish','open','open','','20th-annual-art-and-science-fair-10-may-schoolapalooza-30-may-and-more','','','2014-04-16 09:09:16','2014-04-16 13:09:16','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1216',0,'post','',0),(388,1,'2012-09-27 04:54:30','2012-09-27 04:54:30','','Print','','inherit','open','open','','print-4','','','2012-09-27 04:54:30','2012-09-27 04:54:30','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/shopbutton2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(424,1,'2012-09-28 03:22:16','2012-09-28 03:22:16','','CWSHEADING','','inherit','open','open','','cwsheading','','','2012-09-28 03:22:16','2012-09-28 03:22:16','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/CWSHEADING.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(401,1,'2012-09-27 06:21:41','2012-09-27 06:21:41','','Screen Shot 2012-09-27 at 1.23.46 AM','','inherit','open','open','','screen-shot-2012-09-27-at-1-23-46-am','','','2012-09-27 06:21:41','2012-09-27 06:21:41','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/Screen-Shot-2012-09-27-at-1.23.46-AM.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(402,1,'2012-09-27 06:22:20','2012-09-27 06:22:20','','Screen Shot 2012-09-27 at 1.23.20 AM','','inherit','open','open','','screen-shot-2012-09-27-at-1-23-20-am','','','2012-09-27 06:22:20','2012-09-27 06:22:20','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/Screen-Shot-2012-09-27-at-1.23.20-AM.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(413,1,'2012-09-27 06:50:17','2012-09-27 06:50:17','','CWSCookbook','','inherit','open','open','','cwscookbook','','','2012-09-27 06:50:17','2012-09-27 06:50:17','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/CWSCookbook.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1195,1,'2014-03-24 11:26:49','2014-03-24 15:26:49','<div>\n\n&nbsp;\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000\"><strong>FAMILIES INTERESTED IN THE CHILDREN’S WORKSHOP SCHOOL:  </strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000\"><strong>Our Last School Tours are on Fridays, March 28th, April 4th and April 11th at 9:00AM.</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000\"><strong>PLEASE EMAIL DOROTHY OR JOYCE TO SIGN UP:  dcantwell2@schools.nyc.gov or jborden@schools.nyc.gov</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000\"><strong>We look forward to meeting you!</strong></span></p>\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" alt=\"schoola auction itmes poster\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/schoola-auction-itmes-poster-194x300.jpg\" />\n\n&nbsp;\n\nMarcel is back in NYC for a limited engagement of one night. He and Frank (Franny\'s dad) will be playing at Chris\'s club, <strong>Brooklyn Rod &amp; Gun this evening, March 24<sup>th</sup> at 6:30 59 Kent Ave in Williamsburg</strong>. Adult donation at door $10 goes toward fifth grade yearbooks. Kids are free. The first show is for families. There will be a second session at 8:00 for adults and all parents who want to jam are welcome. Chris (Olive and Arlo\'s dad)  will donate part of bar sales as well.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\">Tues 25 March--Spring picture day!</span></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"font-family: arial;font-size: small;color: #339966\">Tues 25 March 4:45-8pm at Matilda on 11 St near Ave C--Fundraiser for Mr. Scott\'s Experimental Dance Group (EDG). $20 donation--sangria, delicious food and a disco trivia contest!</span></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #339966\"> </span></strong><span style=\"color: #0000ff\">Weds 26 March at 8am in the Library: LETS TALK IN THE LIBRARY-WORKSHOP WITH DOROTHY - Common Core. Leveled books.. What does it mean when my child is reading \"Level M\" books? Accessing The Library Catalog from home. Also come in any time if you would like to talk to Dorothy or look at some of the non fiction texts that we have in our Library. 8:00 am is usually a quiet time!</span>\n\n</div>\n<div><strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">Thursday 27 March at 8:45 in the lobby: Workshop with Valerie Preston, our always dynamic and wise Pre K Social Worker on Developmental Stages, Understanding Your 4, 5, 6 Year Old</span></strong>\n<div>CWS After School Clubs presents: Half-Day Camp Club with Esther–karate, yoga, meditation, art projects at the school on the following half-days: May 16th, June 3rd and June 9th. Pick up at 5pm. $60/day. Please contact Joyce for full information. Please reserve early to save your child/ren spot.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div><em><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: arial;font-size: small;color: #333399;text-decoration: underline\">Karate Club for Adults!!--Karate with Esther on Fridays 1:45-2:30--see Joyce in the office for full info!</span></strong></span></em></div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Thanks to those who have been bringing in auction donations for Schoolapalooza--keep em coming!</div>\n</div>','Fifth-grade yearbook fundraiser tonight at Brooklyn Rod and Gun; Library Workshop with Dorothy-and more!','','publish','open','open','','fifth-grade-yearbook-fundraiser-tonight-at-brooklyn-rod-and-gun-library-workshop-with-dorothy-and-more','','','2014-03-24 11:26:49','2014-03-24 15:26:49','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1195',0,'post','',0),(1200,1,'2014-03-31 18:48:28','2014-03-31 22:48:28','<p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff\"><strong>FAMILIES INTERESTED IN THE CHILDREN’S WORKSHOP SCHOOL:  </strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff\"><strong>Our Last School Tour is on Friday April 11th at 9:00AM.</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff\"><strong>PLEASE EMAIL DOROTHY OR JOYCE TO SIGN UP:  dcantwell2@schools.nyc.gov or jborden@schools.nyc.gov</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff\"><strong>We look forward to meeting you!</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1206\" alt=\"Schoola_call_2014_8\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Schoola_call_2014_8-200x300.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" /></p>\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000\">Thank you to the parents who volunteer in the office and library:</span>  Judy and Sayoko for helping Joyce in the office; late pass writers Nancy, Elizabeth, Susan, Amy and Judy; regular library volunteers Nicole, Lamont and Holly; and those who volunteered to help Dorothy organize and update the collection:  Nancy, Sean, Julie and Beth.  Dorothy also thanks the 4th graders on the Library Squad who are learning how to shelve books and help maintain the library\'s collection!\n\n<span style=\"color: #008080\">As always, thank you to the parents who contribute to Coffee And... every Friday:  Melissa for organizing it; Natalie, Roxanne, Sayoko, Paul and Beth--and to Porto Rico for donating their delicious coffee.  </span>\n\n<span style=\"color: #993366\">Keep those donations coming in for Schoolapalooza!  </span>Save the date--30 May at Clemente Soto Velez Center--live music, great food, courtesy of Stephanie, art and silent auction. Thanks to Cassie for chairing, Rina, Tiffany, Evan, Williams, Kim, Rachel, and Mo for taking leadership roles on the Schoola committee.\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #33cccc\">CWS featured again in the United Federation of Teachers newspaper-</span>-</strong>Casey\'s class and Susan\'s class participated in a memorial for the victims of the Triangle Shirtwaist Fire:\n\nhttp://www.uft.org/news/remembering-legacy-triangle-shirtwaist-factory-fire\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #00ff00\">10 May--11-3pm Arts and Science Fair-fun for the whole family!</span> </strong> The scaffolding should be down by then and we shall celebrate!  Thanks to Judy for chairing, as always!  Email Judy to help out: garnar-wortzel@att.net\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #0000ff\">Important Dates in April:</span></strong>\n\n<span style=\"color: #333399\"><strong>2 April-PTA executive board meeting in lobby after drop-off</strong></span>\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #339966\">9 April-General PTA meeting-after drop off in lobby</span></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #800080\">11 April--deadline for DOE parent surveys--visit Dorothy in the library if you have lost the green envelope given out at family conferences or are in need of internet access to take the survey online</span></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">SPRING BREAK!! 14-22 April!  Back to school on 23 April!  </span></strong> If you need childcare over Spring Break, check out Green Apple Kids Camp .http://www.greenapplekidsny.com/\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #003300\">FUN STUFF TO DO OVER SPRING BREAK AND BEYOND</span></strong>\n\nMuseum of the City of New York: \"City as Canvas\"-graffiti art\n\nAmerican Museum of Natural History: \"The Power of Poison\" and \"Pterosaurus: Flight in the Age of Dinosaurs\"\n\nNew York Botanical Gardens-The Orchid Show\n\nWave Hill: Spring Vacation Week\n\nBrooklyn Children\'s Museum: \"Brooklyn Block Lab\"\n\nFREE!-New York Public Library (42 and 5th): \"The ABC of It: Why Children\'s Books Matter\"-extended til September!\n\nNew York Hall of Science: \"Human Plus: Real Lives and Real Engineering\"\n\nFREE: Central Park Charles A Dana Discovery Center (110 St and 5th Ave): \"Ponds, Pipes and People: Water in Central Park\"\n\nMuseum at Eldridge Street: Scavenger Hunt\n\nFREE: El Museo del Barrio: Super Sabado!--19 April\n\nFREE: Street Games-NYC Parks Dept Thomas Jefferson Park, 114 St and 1st Ave-26 April 11-3pm\n\nLiberty Science Center: \"Beyond Rubik\'s Cube\" starts 26 April til 30 June\n\nBrooklyn Botanical Gardens: Sakura Matsuri, the  Japanese Cherry Blossom Festival--26 and 27 April\n\nThe Morgan Library: \"The Little Prince\" Family Event --27 April\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #0000ff\">FUN AND (MOSTLY) AFFORDABLE SUMMER DAY CAMPS</span></strong>\n<p style=\"text-align: left\">Compiled by Dorothy, Beth, Roxanne and Karen and presented by Dorothy at the March PTA meeting:</p>\n<strong>University Settlement Cornerstone at Campos Plaza</strong>\nFree summer camp and after school activities, field trips, sports, homework help. See Dorothy for flyer.\n\n<strong>Sol Goldman 14th Street Y New Country Day Camp</strong>--buses take the kids to the beautiful Henry Kaufman Campgrounds in Staten Island for sports, swimming, activities.\n<a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=80a4ed7ce5d6423194f5c2ae706358f8&amp;URL=http%3a%2f%2fwww.14streety.org%2fnewcountry%2fnew-country-day-camp%2f\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.14streety.org/newcountry/new-country-day-camp/</a>\n\n<strong>Boys Club of New York Harriman Clubhouse</strong>--a neighborhood institution which provides recreational activities and academic support for boys. 287 East 10 St\n<a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=80a4ed7ce5d6423194f5c2ae706358f8&amp;URL=http%3a%2f%2fwww.bcny.org\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.bcny.org</a>\n\n<strong>Lower East Side Girls Club of NYC-</strong>-for girls 8-18: arts, sports, cultural and life skills programs.\n<a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=80a4ed7ce5d6423194f5c2ae706358f8&amp;URL=http%3a%2f%2fwww.girlsclub.org\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.girlsclub.org</a>\n\n<strong>City Sculpting</strong>--a creative visual arts program with a specialized focus on sculpture.\n<a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=80a4ed7ce5d6423194f5c2ae706358f8&amp;URL=http%3a%2f%2fcitysculpting.com\" target=\"_blank\">http://citysculpting.com</a>\n\n<strong>Butter Beans Food &amp; Garden Summer Camp</strong> is a complete farm to table experience for campers ages 6-10, covering the full spectrum of the food cycle. We are excited to take amazing trips to the Brooklyn Grange, Battery Conservancy, Mother In Law\'s Kimchi, Foraging lead by Leda Meredith, Fine &amp; Raw Chocolates and Ample Hills Ice Cream. Camp runs from July 7th - August 22nd, in two week increments, and is located at 201 West 13th Street. To reserve your spot, email us at camp@butterbeanskitchen.com\n<p style=\"text-align: left\"><strong>Camp Henry:</strong> Henry Street Settlement\'s general day camp--6 weeks 7 July-15 Aug-can do one week or more-\n<a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=80a4ed7ce5d6423194f5c2ae706358f8&amp;URL=http%3a%2f%2fwww.henrystreet.org%2fprograms%2fyouth%2fsummer-day-camps.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.henrystreet.org/programs/youth/summer-day-camps.html</a></p>\n<strong>Abrons Arts Center Barbara L. Tate Arts Camp--a CWS family favorite!</strong> Held at the Henry St Settlement/Abrons Arts Center on Grand St: dance, acting, singing, art, weekly museum visits, weekly swimming. Ages 6 to 12. Early bird special if you register by 25 April. 10% discount for returning campers; 10% discount for siblings.\n<a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=80a4ed7ce5d6423194f5c2ae706358f8&amp;URL=http%3a%2f%2fwww.abronsartscenter.org%2fclasses-and-summer-programs%2fsummer-camps-and-classes.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.abronsartscenter.org/classes-and-summer-programs/summer-camps-and-classes.html</a>\n\n<strong>Oasis camp at PS110 on Delancey St</strong>--sports, swimming every day, arts, field trips\n<a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=80a4ed7ce5d6423194f5c2ae706358f8&amp;URL=http%3a%2f%2fwww.oasischildren.com%2fcamp.php%3fid%3d2\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.oasischildren.com/camp.php?id=2</a>\n<p style=\"text-align: left\"><strong>Rod Rogers Dance Camp</strong>-all dance, all the time-info not out yet-on 4 st and 2 ave\n<a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=80a4ed7ce5d6423194f5c2ae706358f8&amp;URL=http%3a%2f%2fwww.rodrodgersdance.org%2ffall-winter-youth-program-13-14\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.rodrodgersdance.org/fall-winter-youth-program-13-14</a></p>\n<strong>Tada! Summer Week-Long Musical Theater Camps</strong>\n15 West 28 St\n$460 per week 9 June-29 Aug (less if more than 1 week)\nMon-Fri 9:30-2:30 kids rehearse all week and perform the show on Friday.\ntadatheater.com\n\n<strong>United Soccer Academy in McCarren Park in Williamsburg</strong>\n<a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=80a4ed7ce5d6423194f5c2ae706358f8&amp;URL=http%3a%2f%2funitedsocceracademy.com%2f\" target=\"_blank\">http://unitedsocceracademy.com/</a>\n<a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=80a4ed7ce5d6423194f5c2ae706358f8&amp;URL=http%3a%2f%2fwww.usasportgroup.com%2f\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.usasportgroup.com/</a>\n8:00AM until 3:00\nYou can sign up for one week or more, with a total of 4 weeks offered.\n\n<strong>Chelsea Piers</strong>\n<a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=80a4ed7ce5d6423194f5c2ae706358f8&amp;URL=http%3a%2f%2fwww.chelseapiers.com%2fcamp%2fsummer-camp%2fdates-tuition.cfm\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.chelseapiers.com/camp/summer-camp/dates-tuition.cfm</a>\n\n<strong>Soccer/Swim Camp on West Side:</strong>\n<a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=80a4ed7ce5d6423194f5c2ae706358f8&amp;URL=http%3a%2f%2fwww.dusc.net%2fpages%2f\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.dusc.net/pages/</a>\n9:00-5:00\nPier 40, Hudson River &amp; Houston St.\n\n<strong>Mommypoppins Listings</strong>\n\n<a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=80a4ed7ce5d6423194f5c2ae706358f8&amp;URL=http%3a%2f%2fmommypoppins.com%2fnew-york-summer-camp-guide\" target=\"_blank\">http://mommypoppins.com/new-york-summer-camp-guide</a>\n\n<a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=80a4ed7ce5d6423194f5c2ae706358f8&amp;URL=http%3a%2f%2fmommypoppins.com%2fny-kids%2ffree-and-cheap-summer-camps\" target=\"_blank\">http://mommypoppins.com/ny-kids/free-and-cheap-summer-camps</a>\n\n<strong>Children\'s Advocacy Project Listings</strong>\n<a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=80a4ed7ce5d6423194f5c2ae706358f8&amp;URL=http%3a%2f%2fcap4kids.org%2fnewyorkcity%2fparent-handouts%2fafter-school-camps-mentoring\" target=\"_blank\">http://cap4kids.org/newyorkcity/parent-handouts/after-school-camps-mentoring</a>\n<p style=\"text-align: left\"></p>','News for April--Spring Break! and List of Summer Day Camps','','publish','open','open','','news-for-april-spring-break-and-list-of-summer-day-camps','','','2014-03-31 18:48:28','2014-03-31 22:48:28','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1200',0,'post','',0),(1173,1,'2014-03-14 07:40:10','2014-03-14 11:40:10','<p style=\"text-align: center\"><strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">FAMILIES INTERESTED IN THE CHILDREN\'S WORKSHOP SCHOOL:  </span></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">Our Last School Tours are on Fridays, March 28th, April 4th and April 11th at 9:00AM.</span></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">PLEASE EMAIL DOROTHY OR JOYCE TO SIGN UP:  dcantwell2@schools.nyc.gov or jborden@schools.nyc.gov</span></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">We look forward to meeting you!</span></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1174\" alt=\"schoola auction itmes poster\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/schoola-auction-itmes-poster-194x300.jpg\" width=\"194\" height=\"300\" /></p>\n\n<div><strong>Schoolapalooza will be on Friday, MAY 30th at The Clemente Soto Velez Center on the corner of Rivington and Suffolk Streets</strong>. We need you (and your stuff) for the fundraiser auction, which generates about $25,000 for our school\'s budget to help pay for everything from Turtle Bay Music to the CWS Band to Bent on Learning yoga.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>\n<div></div>\n<div>-Hit up your local businesses for gift certificates or merchandise: restaurants, stores, hair stylists!</div>\n<div>-Are you a photographer/teacher/knitter/handy person? Donate your services!</div>\n<div>-Do you or does someone in your family have a vacation home? These are very popular auction items. Donate a long weekend or a week!</div>\n<div>-Donate art! The great artists in our parent community make our auction special!</div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Please bring in your donations of goods, services or gift certificates as soon as you can with the auction donation form filled out.  Extra auction forms at on the bulletin board in the lobby.   Leave auction items  with Joyce in the office or contact Rachel at <a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=bc3a5c9fb638411399dba6b68b8ae3e1&amp;URL=mailto%3arachiefrank515%40yahoo.com\">rachiefrank515@yahoo.com</a>, Tiffany at <a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=bc3a5c9fb638411399dba6b68b8ae3e1&amp;URL=mailto%3azergestiffany%40gmail.com\">zergestiffany@gmail.com</a>, or for ART contact Evan:<a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=bc3a5c9fb638411399dba6b68b8ae3e1&amp;URL=mailto%3aevan%40r20thcentury.com\">evan@r20thcentury.com</a>. For other auction-related questions, contact Cassy: <a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=bc3a5c9fb638411399dba6b68b8ae3e1&amp;URL=mailto%3aneyenesch%40yahoo.com\">neyenesch@yahoo.com</a>.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div><em>Thank you to Cassy, Joyce, Rachel, Tiffany, Evan, Rina, Lori, Mo, Williams, Kim and Stephanie for their hard work planning Schoolapalooza.  If you want to get involved, email Cassy: neyenesch@yahoo.com</em></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div><strong>The Advocacy Committee of the PTA is running a meeting to discuss the issues around the state tests--directly after Community Meeting in the lobby-- today 14 March. </strong> Thank you to Hope, Julie, Eric, Jenny, KerriAnn, Nancy, Bryan and Kim for organizing this talk.  Other meetings to follow!</div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div><strong>Dorothy will be running a workshop on Weds 19 March at 8am to discuss the Common Core standards, as detailed in the  packet handed out by teachers at family conferences</strong>.  If you need another copy, download <strong>A Parent\'s Guide to the Common Core Standards</strong> here:</div>\n<div>http://nyspta.org/pdf/Advocacy/NYSPTA_NYSUT_Common_Core_Brochure_8.13.pdf</div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div><strong>RAFFLE:  Win 2 tickets OR 3 tickets to see The Little Orchestra Society\'s production of <em>Hansel and Gretel</em> at Avery Fisher Hall,</strong> Lincoln Center on Sat 5 April at 11am.  $2 per chance/3 chances for $5.  Raffle tickets sold at Community Meetings--drawing will be 28 March at Community Meeting</div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div><strong>Save the date:  The Arts and Science Fair will be Saturday 10 May in the schoolyard!  </strong>Thanks, as always,  to Judy for chairing!</div>\n<div></div>\n<div><span style=\"color: #0000ff\"><strong>Our pre-k program is featured in The United Federation of Teachers NY Teacher publication!:</strong></span></div>\n<div><span style=\"color: #0000ff\"><strong>http://www.uft.org/feature-stories/lessons-build</strong></span></div>\n<div></div>\n<div><em><strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">Please be sure to do NYC School Survey handed out at Family Conferences.  Take the survey online at:</span></strong></em></div>\n<div><em><strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">nycschoolsurvey.org</span></strong></em></div>\n<div></div>\n<div><em><strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">Your survey access code is on the bottom right hand corner of the first page of the paper copy.  Any troubles, please contact Dorothy.</span></strong></em></div>\n<div><em><strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">Also, please take a survey about the survey by 21 March--see DOE explanation below:</span></strong></em></div>\n<div></div>\n<div>\n<table cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div lang=\"EN-US\">\n\nThe New York City Department of Education is currently exploring ways to better inform parents about school quality, and we are reaching out for your assistance in obtaining feedback from parents about how they use this information to choose and assess schools. The Office of Research, Accountability, and Data have developed a short parent <a href=\"https://survey.vovici.com/se.ashx?s=705E3ED0020246C1\" target=\"_blank\">survey</a>, and we would appreciate your assistance with distributing the survey to parents and encouraging them to complete it.\n\nWe request that parents complete the survey by <b>March 21</b>. We also plan to conduct focus groups with parents on March 26 and April 3 to get more detailed feedback, and the survey asks if parents are available to participate in these sessions. We would welcome as many parents and guardians as can attend.\n\nYou can access the survey here: <a href=\"https://survey.vovici.com/se.ashx?s=705E3ED0020246C1\" target=\"_blank\">https://survey.vovici.com/se.ashx?s=705E3ED0020246C1</a>\n<div><span style=\"color: #0000ff\">CWS Clubs presents:  Half-Day Camp Club with Esther--karate, yoga, meditation, art projects at the school on the following half-days:  21 March, 16 May, 3 June and 9 June.  Pick up at 5pm.  Contact Joyce for full information.</span></div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Thanks to those of you who have attended our workshops and talks about testing, new standards and the Core Curriculum.A quick reminder from Dorothy  about upcoming dates…\nThis Friday, March 21st is a half day. Dismissal 12:10The NY State ELA exam will be given on April 1st, 2nd and 3rd (GRADES 3,4,5)The NY State MATH exam will be given April 31st, May 1ST and 2nd (GRADES 3,4,5)\n\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000\">Workshop with Valerie Preston, Pre K Social Worker</span>\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000\">Developmental Stages, Understanding 4, 5 and 6 Year olds. Tuesday March 25th 9:45 Lobby</span>\n\n<span style=\"color: #0000ff\">LETS TALK IN THE LIBRARY - Common Core. Leveled books.. What does it mean when my child is reading \"Level M\" books? Accessing The Library Catalog from home - Wednesday March 26th, 8:00 am Library</span>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div><span style=\"color: #008000\">Sat 29 March at PS20 (corner of Houston and Essex) from 9-12:30--Workshop for families in District 1 on School Diversity and Equity:</span></div>\n</div>\n<div><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://mail.google.com/mail/u/0/?ui=2&amp;ik=02517e0912&amp;view=att&amp;th=144e05ea42776d3e&amp;attid=0.1&amp;disp=emb&amp;zw&amp;atsh=1\" /></div>\n</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<table cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<table cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td rowspan=\"2\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"3\">\n<table cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div><b> </b></div>\n<div></div></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<table cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td><a href=\"https://mail.google.com/mail/u/0/?shva=1#ad,248\"> </a></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div></div></td>\n<td></td>\n<td>\n<div></div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div></div>\n<div>People (3)</div>\n</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n</div>','Schoolapalooza is Friday 30 May!  Call for Auction Items, Pre-K Class Featured in UFT Newspaper,  Common Core Workshop 19 March at 8am and Other News','','publish','open','open','','schoolapalooza-is-friday-30-may-call-for-auction-items-and-other-news','','','2014-03-14 07:40:10','2014-03-14 11:40:10','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1173',0,'post','',0),(427,1,'2012-09-28 03:30:01','2012-09-28 03:30:01','','FALL 2012 clubs list','','inherit','open','open','','fall-clubs-list-2012','','','2012-09-28 03:30:01','2012-09-28 03:30:01','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/FALL-clubs-list-2012-.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(428,1,'2012-09-28 03:31:09','2012-09-28 03:31:09','','EXTENDED LETTER FALL 2012','','inherit','open','open','','extended-letter-fall-2012','','','2012-09-28 03:31:09','2012-09-28 03:31:09','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/EXTENDED-LETTER-FALL-2012.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(1158,1,'2014-02-13 09:52:33','2014-02-13 14:52:33','Due to the snow, we are cancelling afterschool clubs and test prep today 13 Feb.\n\nFamilies can search the CWS Library collection online--thanks to Dorothy for running a mini-workshop at the PTA meeting last night.  Click on the Catalogue tap to search:\n\nibrary.nycenet.edu/common/servlet/presenthomeform.do?l2m=Home&amp;tm=Home&amp;l2m=Home\n\nIf this link does not work---try:\n\nhttp://www.tinyurl.com/visitthecwslibrary\n\nFamilies applying for kindergarten:  the DOE has extended the deadline to 20 Feb:\n\nhttp://schools.nyc.gov/ChoicesEnrollment/Elementary/Kindergarten\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;','Afterschool Clubs and Test Prep Cancelled for Today, 13 Feb/CWS Library website link/DOE Extends Kindergarten Application Deadline to 20 Feb','','publish','open','open','','afterschool-clubs-and-test-prep-cancelled-for-today-13-febcws-library-website-linkdoe-extends-kindergarten-application-deadline-to-20-feb','','','2014-02-13 09:52:33','2014-02-13 14:52:33','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1158',0,'post','',0),(1161,1,'2014-02-16 18:50:25','2014-02-16 23:50:25','<span style=\"color: #0000ff\">Fun Stuff to Do Over February Break 15-23 Feb:</span>\n\nFREE!--\"Ladies and Gentlemen...The Beatles!\" exhibit at The New York Public Library for the Performing Arts at Lincoln Center--11 Feb til 10 May\n\nFREE!  Urban Park Rangers Kids Week Events--at park locations all over the city:\n\nhttp://www.nycgovparks.org/events/urbanparkrangers\n\nFREE:  New York Public Library main branch on 42nd and 5th:  The ABC of It:  Why Children\'s Books Matter\n\nFREE: The Schomberg Center for Research in Black Culture--2 exhibits--Motown: The Truth is a Hit and Funky Turns 40:  Black Character Revolution\n\nEngineering Week at The New York Hall of Science--make slime! build a rocket!\n\nNew Space Show at the Museum of Natural History--Dark Universe, narrated by Neil DeGrasse Tyson and special exhibit:  The Power of Poison\n\nThe Little Prince:  A New York Story at The Morgan Library 24 Jan-27 April\n\nNew York Botanical Garden:  Culinary Kids Food Festival --activities all week\n\nGraffiti art exhibit \"City as Canvas\" at The Museum of the City of New York\n\n\"Indie Essentials:  25 Must-Play Video Games\" at The Museum of the Moving Image\n\nKids Week at The Intrepid--activities all week long\n\nIce skate!:  Bryant Park, Prospect Park, South Street Seaport\n\n<span style=\"color: #0000ff\">Back to school 24 February!</span>\n\nOur beautiful  library will be closed all week for Dorothy and parent volunteers Lamont, Nicole and Holly to update the collection.  If you can help out one day, please email Dorothy: dcantwell2@childrensworkshopschool.org\n\nCongrats to Darryl LaVare, CWS mom and leader of the Painting and Mural Clubs, who has a show of her paintings at the Micheal Mut Project Space, 97 Avenue C, from 27 Feb til 29 March.  Reception Thurs 27 Feb 6-8pm.\n\nAlso on Thurs 27 Feb, starting at 6pm in the auditorium:  The EVCS Parent Association is hosting a special meeting on the topic of gender expression, led by Jean Malpas, director of the Gender and Families Project at the Ackerman Institute for the Family.  RSVP to parents@evcsnyc.org\n\n<em><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\"><span style=\"color: #ff6600;text-decoration: underline\"><span style=\"color: #008080;text-decoration: underline\"><strong>Friday 28 February:  half day!--12:10 dismissal</strong> <span style=\"color: #000000;text-decoration: underline\">and </span></span></span></span></em><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\"><span style=\"color: #ff6600\"><span style=\"color: #000000;text-decoration: underline\">the third graders will perform their MLK Celebration skits at Community Meeting. Also--it\'s Crayola Storm Day!</span></span></span>\n\n<span style=\"color: #0000ff\">Families interested in The Children\'s Workshop School:  Please email Joyce jborden@schools.nyc.gov  or Dorothy dcantwell2@schools.nyc.gov  to sign up to attend a school tour, held on the following Friday mornings at 9am:  28 Feb, 7 March, 14 March.  We look forward to meeting you!</span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\nI\n\n&nbsp;','Fun Stuff to Do Over February Break----Back to School News--More School Tour Dates','','publish','open','open','','what-to-do-over-february-break-newsreminders-more-school-tour-dates','','','2014-02-16 18:50:25','2014-02-16 23:50:25','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1161',0,'post','',0),(1168,1,'2014-02-28 15:12:54','2014-02-28 20:12:54','<p style=\"text-align: center\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" alt=\"\" src=\"https://gallery.mailchimp.com/22fb0e172fd6d94c84cac8bcd/images/EDGee215c.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"256\" align=\"center\" /></p>\n<strong>Important Dates in March:</strong>\n\n<span style=\"font-family: tahoma\"><strong><strong>Friday March 7th--Martin Luther King Celebration at Community Meeting continues with performances by the 3/4/5, fourth, and fifth graders</strong></strong></span>\n\n<span style=\"font-family: tahoma\"><strong>Tuesday, March 11:  Half day for afternoon family conference - 11:30am pick up - NO CLUBS</strong></span>\n\n<span style=\"font-family: tahoma\"><strong>Wednesday, March 12: PTA Meeting in lobby after drop-off.  Evening family conferences - 3:00pm pick up - NO CLUBS</strong></span>\n\nFriday, March 21: Half day for teacher professional development - 12:10pm pick up - NO CLUBS\n\n<span style=\"font-family: tahoma\"><strong>Thursday March 27:  pre-k non attendance day</strong></span>\n\n<span style=\"color: #008080\"><strong>Anna Howard Shaw School Building Centennial Celebration Planning Meeting-</strong>-<strong>Tues 18 March in library conference room after drop-off:</strong>  Our school building is 100 years old!  In September, all 3 schools:  CWS, EVCS and The Spectrum School will celebrate both the centennial of the building and the removal of the scaffolding with a big party!  If you would like to be involved, email ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org</span>\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #0000ff\">Valerie, our pre-k social worker, will lead a workshop on Understanding Developmental Stages after drop-off on 25 March!</span></strong>\n<table width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<table width=\"600\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=\"left\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\"><strong>You are cordially invited to the second fundraiser for Mr. Scott\'s dance company The Experimental Dance Group at Matilda, owned by CWS family Maristella, Esteban and Matilda. Your $20 donation will include a complimentary drink as well as assorted appetizers which include: fried calamari, quesadilla, and pizza. What a wonderful way to have fun after work and all for a good cause while listening to real disco music. Don\'t forget to participate in the disco trivia contest to win an E.D.G. T-shirt! See you there. </strong><strong>Where: Matilda Restaurant 647 East 11th Street (between Ave B and Ave C)</strong>\n<strong>When: March 25th, 2014</strong>\n<strong>Time: 4:45 pm to 8:00 pm</strong></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<table width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=\"left\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">&nbsp;\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" alt=\"\" src=\"https://gallery.mailchimp.com/22fb0e172fd6d94c84cac8bcd/images/dirty_wars_soshe336f8.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" align=\"center\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><strong>Congratulations to CWS parent David Riker (Maria and alum Laila\'s  dad!) who co-wrote the screenplay</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><strong> to the Oscar-nominated documentary Dirty Wars. </strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://gallery.mailchimp.com/22fb0e172fd6d94c84cac8bcd/images/schoola.jpg\" width=\"499\" align=\"center\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">The Children\'s Workshop School\'s annual evening fundraiser Schoolapalooza is on May 30th at the Clemente Soto Velez Center!!  To volunteer to help out, email ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org</span></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">Thank you to Cassy for being the Schoola Chair!</span></strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>','News for March:  Family Conferences, Experimental Dance Group Fundraiser at Matilda, Understanding Developmental Stages Workshop with Valerie','','publish','open','open','','news-for-march-family-conferences-experimental-dance-group-fundraiser-at-matilda-understanding-developmental-stages-workshop-with-valerie','','','2014-02-28 15:12:54','2014-02-28 20:12:54','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1168',0,'post','',0),(913,1,'2013-08-09 12:41:49','2013-08-09 16:41:49','[caption id=\"attachment_918\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-918 aligncenter\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/photo-300x224.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"224\" /> Spring 2013 Let\'s Paint a Mural Club\'s Mural at Campos Garden[/caption]\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><strong>The Children’s Workshop School Update</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><strong></strong><strong>For Back-to-School 2013</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><a href=\"http://www.childrensworkshopschool.org/\">http://www.childrensworkshopschool.org</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\">212-614-9531 or <a href=\"mailto:ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org\">ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\">”We’re all a family under one sky!”</p>\n<strong>For prospective families:  </strong>Looking for a kindergarten spot for your child?  We still have a limited number of kindergarten seats for the 2013/2014 school year.  Limited seats are available in grades 1-4 as well.  Due to construction, our school office will not be open until 25 August.  Please email Dorothy, our parent coordinator, with your information to find out how to go about applying for these seats: <a href=\"mailto:dcantwell2@schools.nyc.gov\">dcantwell2@schools.nyc.gov</a>.  If you are looking for a pre-kindergarten or kindergarten spot for next school year, 2014/2015 please check our website, childrensworkshopschool.org, in September for tour dates, which will begin in October.\n\n<strong>For all members of the CWS community: </strong> Get on the bus!  <strong>Join the 50<sup>th</sup> Anniversary of the March on Washington for Jobs and Freedom, where MLK gave his “I Have a Dream” speech that inspired Maria and Jean to found our school.  Saturday 24 August</strong>—buses leave for Washington DC at 4 am. Email Beth for transportation info: c<a href=\"mailto:co-president1@childrensworkshopschool.org\">o-president1@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>\n\n<span style=\"color: #800080\"> <strong>Welcome to new and returning families!</strong>  <strong>Here’s what you need to know for back-to-school—and other news:</strong></span>\n\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000\"><strong><em>Teacher letters are set to go out in the mail on 20 August.</em></strong></span>\n\n<strong><em> </em></strong><span style=\"color: #000000\"><strong>The auditorium will be finished!</strong>  </span>Thanks to the team of renovators, we will once again hold our weekly Friday Community Meetings in the auditorium but now with state-of-the-art sound and light system, all-new stage, seating, floor, ceiling.  We all must observe a new rule:  no food or drink allowed in the auditorium, ever.  See our website, childrensworkshopschool.org, for photos taken by Joyce in July—it looks amazing!\n\nWe will also have <strong>Smartboards</strong> and a new set of laptops from a RESO-A grant—thanks to the Tech Team (made up of parents and teachers) for their hard work and Councilwoman Rosie Mendez for her constant support of our school.  We won another RESO-A grant so that for next school year (14/15), we will have Smartboards in every classroom.\n\n<strong>Congrats to Chris</strong>—he is officially our new Building Manager.  Also, thanks to Hope’s tireless advocacy, we will <strong>continue to have two school safety officers, Officer Baptiste and Officer Das.</strong>\n\n<strong> </strong><strong>Baby news:</strong>  Michelle M. had a baby girl, Alexa Rose and Michelle F. had twins (!):  Matthew and Mason.  Congrats to both families!\n\n<strong><em>Afterschool Clubs will start Monday 16 September—thanks to Joyce, Rachel and Daryl! Here\'s the Fall Club offerings--please note that Darryl\'s Painting Projects Club on Monday, her Let\'s Paint a Mural Club on Weds and Patrizia\'s Dance Improvisation Club on Thursdays are all open to grades 1-5:</em></strong>\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/cws-fall-13-clubs1.pdf\">http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/cws-fall-13-clubs1.pdf</a>\n\n<strong><em>If you can help out with Afterschool Clubs registration on the mornings of 11 and 12 September, please email Rachel: </em></strong> <a href=\"mailto:Rachel@dancewithrachel.com\">Rachel@dancewithrachel.com</a>\n\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000\"><strong>FIRST WEEK OF SCHOOL:</strong></span>\n\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000\"><strong>9 Sept:</strong></span>  <strong>first day of school –half day for pre-k and k; full day for grades 1-5.  Pre-k and k drop off in their classrooms; for grades 1-5 drop-off and pick up will continue to be in the lobby.  <em>Look for Dorothy, our parent coordinator, in the lobby after drop-off for help with questions and to give separation-anxiety comfort.</em></strong>\n\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000\"><strong>10 Sept</strong>:</span>  <strong>half-day for pre-k; full day for k-5—Dorothy will again be in the lobby after drop-off</strong>\n\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000\"><strong>11 Sept:</strong></span>  <strong>full day for all students.  Afterschool Clubs registration in the lobby in the morning.  No need to rush to be first in line; if a club is overenrolled, it goes to a lottery. Clubs start Monday 16 September.  See Fall 13 Afterschool Clubs offerings on our website, childrensworkshopschool.org</strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">12 Sept:</span> Afterschool Clubs registration continues in the lobby in the morning.</strong>\n\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000\"><strong><em>13 Sept:  All-Family Welcome Breakfast and PTA Meeting in the lobby after drop-off.  Meet the PTA Executive Board and find out the many ways you can get involved at CWS!</em></strong></span>\n\nEnjoy the rest of your summer!  Any questions/concerns/ideas please email <a href=\"mailto:ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org\">ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;','CWS Back to School Update!','','publish','open','open','','cws-back-to-school-update','','','2013-08-09 12:41:49','2013-08-09 16:41:49','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=913',0,'post','',0),(993,1,'2013-10-18 14:38:33','2013-10-18 18:38:33','Today, we held the first Community Meeting in the renovated auditorium--and the first song was a rousing rendition of \"We\'re All a Family Under One Sky!\"  Photos to be posted soon.\n\nTonight, all members of the CWS community are invited to attend a fundraiser at The Shala at Union Sq for our school\'s Bent on Learning yoga program--children are welcome.  $25 suggested donation per family.\n\nTomorrow --Harvest Fest!\n\nFamilies interested in The Children\"s Workshop School, please email Joyce jborden@schools.nyc.gov or Dorothy dcantwell2@schools.nyc.gov to sign up for a  tour.  Upcoming  dates:  Monday 28 October at 8:15am; Monday  4 November at 8:15; Friday 8 November at 9:00am; Friday  15 November  at 9:00.','The Auditorium is Open!!--Bent on Learning Yoga Benefit for CWS Tonight--Harvest Festival Tomorrow--School Tour Schedule','','publish','open','open','','the-auditorium-is-open-bent-on-learning-yoga-benefit-for-cws-tonight-harvest-festival-tomorrow-school-tour-schedule','','','2013-10-18 14:38:33','2013-10-18 18:38:33','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=993',0,'post','',0),(1002,1,'2013-10-21 11:55:38','2013-10-21 15:55:38','<span style=\"color: #000000\">Thanks to all for a wonderful <strong>Harvest Festival!  </strong>We had daffodil bulb planting and tortilla-making in Campos Garden; square dancing in the school yard; fantastic food; fun arts and crafts--it was a great day of family fun!</span>\n\n<span style=\"color: #3366ff\"><em><strong>Families interested in The Children\'s Workshop School, please email Joyce jborden@schools.nyc.gov or Dorothy dcantwell2@schools.nyc.gov to sign up for a  tour.  We look forward to meeting you!</strong></em></span>\n\n<span style=\"color: #3366ff\"><em><strong>Upcoming  dates:  </strong></em></span>\n\n<span style=\"color: #3366ff\"><em><strong>Mondays at 8:15am:   28 October; 4 November; 2 December; 16 December; 6 January; 27 January; 10 February; 24 February </strong></em></span>\n\n<span style=\"color: #3366ff\"><em><strong>Fridays at 9:00am: 8 November; 6 December; 20 December; 10 January; 24 January; 7 February and 28 February.</strong></em></span>\n\n<strong>CWS Parents/Families:  please note that our phone lines are down again due to the ongoing issues from the Hurricane Sandy flooding on the Lower East Side.  The DOE Office of Telecommunication has supplied us with 3 cell phones--2 for the office:  (917) 324-5713 and (917) 386-4798 and one for Mavis, our school nurse:  (917) 913-0274.  Please use these numbers to get in touch with the school if you have an emergency.</strong>','CWS School Tour Dates--Emergency School Cell Phone Numbers','','publish','open','open','','upcoming-cws-school-tour-dates-emergency-school-cell-phone-numbers','','','2013-10-21 11:55:38','2013-10-21 15:55:38','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1002',0,'post','',0),(1010,1,'2013-12-05 23:07:18','2013-12-06 04:07:18','<em><strong>We have posted the tour dates on the school tour page: Check out: <a title=\"School Tours\" href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/admissions/school-tours/\">ADMISSIONS&gt;SCHOOL TOURS</a></strong></em>\n\n<em><strong>Families interested in The Children’s Workshop School, please email Joyce  (<a href=\"mailto:jborden@schools.nyc.gov\" target=\"_blank\">jborden@schools.nyc.gov</a>)or Dorothy (<a href=\"mailto:dcantwell2@schools.nyc.gov\" target=\"_blank\">dcantwell2@schools.nyc.gov</a>) to sign up for a  tour.  We look forward to meeting you!</strong></em>\n\n<em><strong>Upcoming  dates:  </strong></em>\n\n<em><strong>Mondays at 8:15am:  16 December 2013; 6 January, 2014; 27 January 2014; 10 February 2014; 24 February 2014</strong></em>\n\n<em><strong>Fridays at 9:00am: 6 December 2013; 20 December 2013; 10 January 2014; 24 January 2014; 7 February 2014 and 28 February 2014.</strong></em>\n\n&nbsp;','School Tour Dates Updated','','publish','open','open','','school-tour-dates-updated','','','2013-12-05 23:07:18','2013-12-06 04:07:18','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1010',0,'post','',0),(967,1,'2013-09-26 16:13:36','2013-09-26 20:13:36','<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/the-childrens-workshop-school-second-re-annual-harvest-festival-saturday-19-october/cwsharvestfestival2013-1/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-968\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-968\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/cwsharvestfestival2013-1-229x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"229\" height=\"300\" /></a>\n\nHarvest Festival pricing:  Food will vary in price.  POP (pay-one-price)  for activities:  $15 for 1 child/$20 for 2 children/$25 for 3+ children (must be from same family; cousins not included!  spit sisters/blood brothers not included!)  OR pay per activity, $1 per ticket (# of tix per activity will vary)\n\nTo volunteer to help out at the Harvest Festival, please email Rina rinaortega4@gmail.com or Elizabeth edowner@earthlink.net.\n\n&nbsp;','The Children\'s Workshop School Second Re-Annual Harvest Festival!  Saturday 19 October','','publish','open','open','','the-childrens-workshop-school-second-re-annual-harvest-festival-saturday-19-october','','','2013-09-26 16:13:36','2013-09-26 20:13:36','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=967',0,'post','',0),(986,1,'2013-10-04 16:32:35','2013-10-04 20:32:35','Please note the Tech Team met and reconsidered the date of the Mixer/PTA Meeting, changing it from Fri 11 Oct to Mon 28 October from  6-8pm--no childcare provided (the other evening PTA meetings will have childcare).','Change of date for Tech Team-sponsored Mixer/PTA Meeting:  now Monday 28 October 6-8pm','','publish','open','open','','change-of-date-for-tech-team-sponsored-mixerpta-meeting-now-monday-28-october-6-8pm','','','2013-10-04 16:32:35','2013-10-04 20:32:35','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=986',0,'post','',0),(988,1,'2013-10-08 12:25:20','2013-10-08 16:25:20','<p align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/october-update/cwsharvestfestival2013-1-2/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-989\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-989\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/cwsharvestfestival2013-1-229x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"229\" height=\"300\" /></a></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>The Children’s Workshop School Update</strong></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>For October 2013</strong></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://www.childrensworkshopschool.org/\">http://www.childrensworkshopschool.org</a></p>\n<p align=\"center\">212-614-9531 or <a href=\"mailto:ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org\">ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org</a></p>\n<p align=\"center\">”We’re all a family under one sky!”</p>\n<strong>October will be a wonderful month for CWS!</strong>  Now that our children are settled into their classroom routines, having formed the all-important bond with their teachers and classmates, we can come together as a community to square dance, make crafts and eat great food at <strong>our Second Re-Annual Harvest Festival on Saturday 19 October from 11-3.  Bring friends and family—all are welcome!  </strong>Later in the month will be the <strong>Technology Team-sponsored Mixer/PTA Meeting starting at 6:00pm on Monday 28 October—adults only!</strong>\n\nThank you to Joyce, Sonia, Jed and Christopher for providing childcare on <strong>Curriculum Night</strong> and to Judy and Ian for making the snack run.  Thank you to Hope for writing the CWS Safety Brochure.\n\nDorothy has the <strong>library </strong>up and running-thank you to those parents who have volunteered to shelve books and help maintain the library’s collection.  Please be sure your child(ren) return their library contracts.\n\nPlease <strong>return lunch forms to the office</strong>, if you have not already.  If you need another copy, please see Dorothy in the library.  Also, fifth grade parents, if you have not already spoken with Dorothy about the middle school application process, please visit her in the library or email her: dcantwell2@schools.nyc.gov.\n\nCongrats to Angie and Kaylee, both in Molly’s class—they each won a Rainbow Loom!  Be on the lookout for <strong>more PTA raffles—Minecraft Legos!</strong>—every single penny goes right back to our children.  Coming up in a month or so: <strong>we will raffle off  2 tickets to see the Little Orchestra Society’s production of <em>Firebird</em>  at Lincoln Center (Sun 24 Nov at noon—1 hour long--perfect for ages 4+--excellent seats---$50 value).</strong>\n\n<strong>Coffee And…the Book Sale</strong> is (almost) every Friday before Community Meeting, thanks to Melissa, Natalie, Roxanne, Sayoko and the many parents who donate.\n\n<strong><em>Great news!:  we will have air conditioners by May/June in every classroom—in the library—in the office!—all thanks to our After-School Clubs budget surplus.</em></strong>\n\nThank you to the Manhattan Borough President’s office, which has supplied our teachers with <strong>Youth Bucks coupons redeemable for $2 worth of Union Square Greenmarket produce</strong>. Classes will be taking walks to the Greenmarket to spend their bucks.\n\nOur first school-wide lice check of the year will be on 8 Oct.  Thank you to Nancy for coordinating and Judy, Rachel and Lori for helping out.  Remember, there is no shame or blame when it comes to lice and the sooner we get rid of them, the less likely they will spread.\n\nPlease tell your <strong>3/4/5<sup>th</sup> graders to be on the lookout for classroom visits from Ed, our CWS Band Director (18 years and counting!) and Terry, our Turtle Bay Music School teacher</strong>, as they will invite the children to join the <strong>Band and Chorus</strong>, both of which meet during school hours<strong>.  No experience necessary</strong>—all 3/4/5<sup>th</sup> grade students are eligible to join Chorus or Band <strong>(instruments supplied by our school</strong>, thanks in part to a VH-1 grant).  Those who join must commit to <strong>regular and dedicated practice</strong>! Once the Band is organized, we would like a parent to serve as Band Parent and help coordinate communication between Ed and band members.\n\n<strong>Thank you to Bent on Learning, </strong>our yoga program:  <strong>Bent on Learning  is hosting a fundraiser for CWS--Friday 18 October from 6:30-9pm at The Shala Union Square, 815 Broadway, second floor; $50 suggested donation.  </strong>6:30-7:30 participate in a vinyasa/restorative class then at 7:45 enjoy music by Charlie Burnham, a singer and violinist.\n\n<strong>Swim classes will start 15 October for the 2<sup>nd</sup> graders</strong> at the Asser Levy pool on 23<sup>rd</sup> Street, thanks to the NYC Department of Parks and Recreation Swim for Life program.  <strong>The third graders have started doing Reading Buddies with the pre-k children</strong>—Molly’s students are matched with Suma’s students and Miriam’s students are matched with Helen’s.\n\nCheck out the <strong>New York Public Library’s list of 100 Great Children’s Books (in abc order)</strong>:\n\n<a href=\"http://www.nypl.org/childrens100\">http://www.nypl.org/childrens100</a>\n\n<strong>Turtle Bay Music School is having its annual Halloween Open House on Sat 26 Oct from 12-3</strong> at 244 East 52 Street between 2<sup>nd</sup> and 3<sup>rd</sup> Avenues—take 6 or M trains or M15 bus.  To RSVP(and you must rsvp), fill out form in link:\n\n<a href=\"http://www.tbms.org/event/halloween-open-house/\">http://www.tbms.org/event/halloween-open-house/</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong><em>WEEK of 5 October:</em></strong>\n\nAll week long is <strong>Parents as Partners Week</strong>, sponsored by the NYC Department of Education—Chancellor Walcott scheduled to speak on 10 Oct--see all activities/meetings here.\n\n<a href=\"http://schools.nyc.gov/ParentsFamilies/ParentsasPartnersOctober2013\">http://schools.nyc.gov/ParentsFamilies/ParentsasPartnersOctober2013</a>\n\nTues 8 October:  All-school lice check\n\n<strong><em>Week of 14 October:</em></strong>\n\nMon 14 October—no school-Columbus Day\n\nFriday 18 October—School Leadership Team meeting 7:30am in Suma’s classroom\n\n<strong><em>Saturday 19 October—Harvest Festival!  11-3 in the school yard, cafeteria and lobby—rain or shine! Harvest Festival pricing: entry is free; entertainment is free. Food will vary in price. POP (pay-one-price) for activities: $15 for 1 child/$20 for 2 children/$25 for 3+ children (must be from same family; cousins not included! spit sisters/blood brothers not included!) OR pay per activity, $1 per ticket (# of tix per activity will vary)</em></strong>\n\n<strong>Week of 21 October:</strong>\n\nWeds 23 October:  picture day!  Do not wear green! (Please note that Miriam’s and Chrystal’s classes will take their all-class photos on 15 October)\n\nThursday 24 October:  no school for pre-k\n\n<strong>Week of 28 October:</strong>\n\n<strong><em>Monday 28 October Tech Team-sponsored PTA Mixer/Meeting 6-8pm in lobby.  This is a child-free event; our only one of the school year.</em></strong>\n\nPlease note that<strong> at The Children’s Workshop School, we do not honor any holidays other than birthdays and Martin Luther King Day (with our All-School Living the Dream Celebration). Please do not send your child(ren) to school in costume on Halloween</strong>—have a great time celebrating Halloween after school.\n\n<strong><em>Looking Forward…the November update will go out in mailchimp, thanks to the efforts of Veronica and Keiko:</em></strong>\n\n5 Nov-Election Day, no school\n\n6 Nov-PTA Exec Board Meeting in Library Conference Room after drop-off\n\n11 Nov-Veteran’s Day-no school\n\n13 Nov-PTA General Meeting after drop-off in lobby (note change of date from 20 Nov)\n\n22 Nov-half day for Staff Weekend Retreat-pickup time TBA\n\n28 and 29 Nov-no school—Happy Thanksgiving!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;','October Update','','publish','open','open','','october-update','','','2013-10-08 12:25:20','2013-10-08 16:25:20','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=988',0,'post','',0),(924,1,'2013-08-26 10:01:31','2013-08-26 14:01:31','<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/latest-photo-of-the-auditorium-wow/photo-5/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-925\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-925\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/photo-5-224x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"224\" height=\"300\" /></a>\n\nThanks to Joyce for documenting the progress and to the team of renovators!','Latest Photo of the Auditorium:  Wow!','','publish','open','open','','latest-photo-of-the-auditorium-wow','','','2013-08-26 10:01:31','2013-08-26 14:01:31','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=924',0,'post','',0),(952,1,'2013-09-11 16:29:06','2013-09-11 20:29:06','Please join us for the Welcome Breakfast and first PTA meeting of the school year on Friday 13 September after drop-off!  Enjoy coffee, thanks to the generosity of Porto Rico, and treats, thanks to the generosity of our longtime families.  Meet the PTA executive board,  committee chairs and our teachers and staff.  Find out the many ways your family can contribute to CWS!','PTA Welcome Breakfast/First PTA Meeting on Friday 13 September after drop-off','','publish','open','open','','pta-welcome-breakfastfirst-pta-meeting-on-friday-13-september-after-drop-off','','','2013-09-11 16:29:06','2013-09-11 20:29:06','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=952',0,'post','',0),(959,1,'2013-09-24 07:26:59','2013-09-24 11:26:59','Wednesday, 2 October is Curriculum Night--childcare provided\n\nFriday, 11 October from 6-8 in the lobby  is the Technology Team-sponsored PTA Mixer/Meeting--adults only\n\nSaturday 19 October is the Second Re-Annual Children\'s Workshop School Harvest Festival!  Make a scarecrow-- paint a pumpkin---squaredance--eat great food!  To volunteer to help out, email Rina rinaortega4@gmail.com or Elizabeth edowner@earthlink.net\n\n&nbsp;','SAVE THE DATES!!','','publish','open','open','','save-the-date-saturday-19-october-is-the-harvest-festival','