y: tahoma;font-size: small\">Talent Show: Jen, Scott, Robert, Beth</span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\">Centennial Celebration: Beth, Elizabeth, Trina, Keiko, Rina, Robert, Dorothy and Joyce</span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\">Those who help out with everything: Roxanne, Lori, Paul, Margot, Natalie, Rosie, Gabby, Scott, Satya, Sean, Ally, Eric, Chris, Irene, Julie, Williams, Peter, Mike, Tomo, Roka, Shahad, Steve, Tom, Risa, Sveta, Mo, Theresa, Rick, Ann, Sabine, Chris, David, Alex, Trina, Kasumi, Vanessa, Shay, and Andrew</span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">Thank you to Ed for directing the CWS Band; Terry from Turtle Bay Music School for giving music instruction to all students and directing the CWS Chorus; Sarah and Kirsten our ArtsConnection teaching artists; and Shelley and Emilio our Bent on Learning yoga teachers.</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">The Children\'s Workshop School PTA Exec Board for 14/15:</span></strong>  Rina and Beth, co-presidents; Elizabeth, vice-president; Tiffany and Darryl, co-secretaries; Keiko and Natasha, co-vice presidents.  Email us: <span style=\"color: #ff0000\"><strong>ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org</strong></span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><strong><span style=\"color: #008000\">FALL 2014 AFTER-SCHOOL CLUB CHOICES WILL BE POSTED BY 8 July!</span></strong></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Last Dates in June:</strong></div>\n<strong><span style=\"color: #0000ff\">Tues 24 June-Pre-k  orientation for new families--welcome! We are happy to have you at The Children\'s Workshop School!</span></strong>\n\n<strong>Weds 25 June–3/4/5 Grade Talent Show:  The CWS Band, The CWS Chorus, The Improvisational Dance Club and 10 acts ranging from classical piano, violin and cello performances to gymnastics to singing and dancing to lightening-fast Rubik\'s Cube unscrambling!  FREE (donations always welcome).  Doors open at 5:30pm for refreshments in the lobby; show starts at 6pm in the auditorium.</strong>\n\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000\"><em><strong>Thursday 26 June -last day of school, 11:30 dismissal! Thank you to Maria, Dorothy, Joyce, Sonia and all of our teachers and staff, our school safety officers, kitchen staff, and custodial staff for a wonderful year!  </strong></em></span>\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #0000ff\">Happy summer!  Public pools open 27 June–free lunch available to kids all summer long at the pools–Tompkins Square; Dry Dock; Hamilton Fish; among others–also free swimming classes for kids at the public pools!</span></strong>\n\n<strong><em>Looking forward to next school year 14/15–teacher letters will be mailed out in late August.  Important dates in September:</em></strong>\n\n4 September is the first day of school\n\n4 and 5 September–join Dorothy and the PTA executive board for Coffee and Conversation on Tar Beach after drop off\n\n9 Sept -CWS Tech Team Mixer–6-8pm–all parents invited –SmartBoard demonstration and refreshments on Tar Beach\n\n9 and 10 September--after school clubs registration in the morning before drop-off\n\n12 Sept (tentative)-first PTA meeting –after drop-off in lobby–meet our PTA committee chairs, School Leardership Team (SLT) members; teachers and staff\n\n15 September--first day of after-school clubs.\n\n17 September--first District 1 Community Education Council meeting--Town Hall discussion of School Diversity\n\nSaturday 20 September 11-3:  Centennial Celebration of the Anna Howard Shaw School Building–all 3 schools in the building collaborating on a family fun day!\n\n25 and 26 Sept-no school -Rosh Hashanah','Congratulations to our 5th Graders on Moving Up to Middle School!--PTA thank yous--September-save-the-dates','','publish','open','open','','congratulations-to-our-5th-graders-on-moving-up-to-middle-school-pta