s for Middle School has officially begun! \n\nThe District One Middle School Directory has been posted on line (translations available http://schools.nyc.gov/ChoicesEnrollment/Middle/default.htm and hard copies will be arriving at the school soon! Or Go to www.schools.nyc.gov click Enrollment, then Middle School on the left menu.\n\nMany of you have been visiting middle schools, doing on-line research and talking to each other and to seasoned parents of middle school students…all in an effort to find the right middle school for your child. Your research and school visits should be done early in the Fall and the applications themselves are due in December, so there is not a lot of time…\n\nThe process should be similar to last year’s process; although there are always a few changes, but briefly:\n\n•	If your child attends a District One School (CWS!) and is a resident of District One, you may apply to A District One Middle School. (The application will be distributed through CWS).\n\n•	If your child attends a District One School (CWS!) but is a resident of ANOTHER District, you may apply to a District One Middle Schools AND to schools in your district of residence.  (The application will be preprinted with all your choices, and distributed through CWS).\n\n•	Everyone can also apply to schools like NEST and ICE and any other schools that accept citywide applications. Those applications are handled by the schools themselves and sometimes involve a different process and have different deadlines. The same is true for charter, private and parochial schools.\n\n	In the past, application to schools outside your district has not been possible.  Occasionally, such requests have been handled separately and after the application process has been completed.  If you are interested in a school not in your district you must ask them on a tour  how and if they accept Out of District applications at all.\n\nWhat you should be doing now is research, making appointment for tours, looking at schools, networking with other parents and most importantly, reflecting on who your child is and where they will thrive.  Again, the link to middle school enrollment on the DOE website is    \n     http://schools.nyc.gov/ChoicesEnrollment/Middle/default.htm \nMost important information can be found in the directory, which will go home in backpacks soon. I have also included a list of Middle School Fairs which you should consider attending, depending on your district of residence, a flier for the District One Middle School Fair, a flier from TSMS. ESCHS, another popular school is taking online registrations for tours at http://www.eschs.org/  Click ABOUT then ADMISSIONS.\n\nDistrict One Middle School Fair will be October 9th \n\n\nI will be holding 2 meetings to get you started. \nMonday, September 29   3:30  pm Library\nTuesday, September 30th 8:30 am  Library\n\nI am also always available for private discussions and I plan to meet with each family individually to answer the questions you will have, at some point in the process.\n Look for me during Curriculum Night, ( September 23rd, 2014)\nOr  Please E mail me at Dcantwell2@schools.nyc.gov. \nOr Call me at 212 674 3820 ext 4081.\n\n I wish you the best as you go through this process and I want to offer you words of encouragement. You know your child and there are lots of choices. Our acceptance rate in the past has been great and our alumni are doing us proud. It’s all good.\n\nBut don’t wait! The more you do early, the easier the process will be.\n\nDorothy Cantwell, Parent Coordinator\nChildren’s Workshop School \n212 674 3820 ext 4081\nDcantwell2@schools.nyc.gov \n\nAnd don’t forget to check in regularly at our websites\nwww.childrensworkshopschool.org    and  http://schools.nyc.gov/schoolportals/01/m361/default.htm\n \n\n','MIDDLE SCHOOL NEWS','','publish','open','open','','middle-school-news','','','2014-09-29 13:47:19','2014-09-29 17:47:19','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1399',0,'post','',0),(562,1,'2012-10-10 09:56:18','2012-10-10 13:56:18','','Amazon Logo','','inherit','open','open','','picture-18','','','2012-10-10 09:56:18','2012-10-10 13:56:18','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/Picture-18.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1305,1,'2014-07-07 16:34:21','2014-07-07 20:34:21','Welcome to the Childrens Workshop School Library!To browse our catalog, please visit\n<a href=\"http://www.tinyurl.com/VISITTHECWSLIBRARY\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.tinyurl.com/VISITTHECWSLIBRARY</a>','WELCOME TO THE LIBRARY!','','publish','open','open','','welcome-to-the-library','','','2014-07-07 16:34:21','2014-07-07 20:34:21','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1305',0,'post','',0),(1351,1,'2014-08-09 10:07:51','2014-08-09 14:07:51','<img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1360\" alt=\"CENTENNIALFLYER2lowres\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/CENTENNIALFLYER2lowres-231x300.jpg\" width=\"231\" height=\"300\" />\n\n<span style=\"color: #0000ff\"><strong>Now that the scaffolding is down, we can celebrate the 100th birthday and rich history of our school building, named for Anna Howard Shaw (doctor, minister, women\'s rights leader), on Saturday 20 September from 12-4!  All three schools are collaborating on a fun day of activities and events.</strong></span>\n\n<strong>Please help out by <span style=\"color: #ff0000\">making savory food </span>(like chili, empanadas, rice balls) or <span style=\"color: #ff0000\">desserts</span> (cookies, cupcakes) or donate your time and talents by <span style=\"color: #ff0000\">helping with set up and clean up</span> or <span style=\"color: #ff0000\">facepainting</span> or <span style=\"color: #ff0000\">work on the stage crew</span> for the  auditorium events.</strong>\n\n<strong>Please email <span style=\"color: #008000\">ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org </span>to volunteer.</strong>\n\n<strong>Thank you!</strong>\n\nLooking forward to the first day of