 I will donate $100.00 monthly</option> <option value=\"4: I will donate\">4: I will donate $200.00 monthly</option> <option value=\"5: I will donate\">5: I will donate $300.00 monthly</option> </select></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"currency_code\" value=\"USD\" />\n<input type=\"image\" name=\"submit\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/recurring.jpg\" alt=\"PayPal - The safer, easier way to pay online!\" /><img src=\"https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/scr/pixel.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" border=\"0\" />\n\n</form>Thank you so much for your contribution and supporting public education and CWS! Contact the PTA and volunteer to help out our school. If you need assistance with your paypal transactions, please contact <a href=\"mailto:donations@childrensworkshopschool.org\">donations@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>. We are always looking to partner with our community and businesses to make CWS the best school that it can be. Thank you in advance for your donation and interest. CWS kids rock!','Are You Sure?','','publish','open','open','','areyousure','','','2012-09-25 06:35:25','2012-09-25 06:35:25','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?page_id=181',0,'page','',0),(183,1,'2012-09-25 06:36:03','2012-09-25 06:36:03','<strong><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\">Thank you sincerely for your contributions to CWS!</span> </strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n\nWe hope to see you at our PTA meetings and events! Please check with your child(ren)\'s teacher for an upcoming event in your classroom! Your presence at these events are a way to show your support!\n\nThank you again!\n','Thank you!','','publish','open','open','','thankyou','','','2012-09-25 06:36:03','2012-09-25 06:36:03','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?page_id=183',0,'page','',0),(189,1,'2012-09-25 06:45:11','2012-09-25 06:45:11','The Children\'s Workshop School, founded in 1993, is a progressive public elementary school located on the East Village of Manhattan. CWS strives for students to be open-minded and compassionate; to gain a sense of themselves and others; and to understand and appreciate the diversity of the community. Children are guided and supported to fulfill their creative, physical, emotional, social and intellectual potential. Our goal is for our children to recognize that they have the power and resources to effect change. It is our hope that children will grow to be responsible, critical and caring members of a pluralistic society.','About CWS','','publish','open','closed','','aboutcws','','','2012-09-25 06:45:11','2012-09-25 06:45:11','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?page_id=189',0,'page','',0),(191,1,'2012-09-25 06:48:42','2012-09-25 06:48:42','The Children\'s Workshop School is considered to be one of the \"best-kept secrets in New York.\" An alternative \"choice\" public school for children from pre-kindergarten through fifth grade, it was formed by Maria Velez-Clarke and Jean Finnerty who wanted to give families in the Lower East Side access to a progressive, smaller, child-centered public school. The two educators had worked together at Central Park East and shared a vision of dynamic, and progressive education.\n\nMaria Velez-Clarke became Principal of the Children\'s Workshop School and her consistent vision, profound and insightful knowledge of children, and experience as an educator continue to inform and guide CWS as it grows and evolves. Jean Finnerty has since relocated to Finland, where she teaches at the Kesamaki School. The two educators have remained in close contact, sharing news and ideas and have brainstormed about how their students can form cross-cultural bonds.\n\nCWS opened its doors in September 1993. It began at the Goldman Y, on 14th Street and 1st Avenue, eventually moving into the under-utilized Anna Howard Shaw building at 610 East 12th Street. This challenging beginning and transition did not discourage families who chose to be pioneers in the establishment and development of our school, which has grown from those first 80 students and their families to the 265+ students and their families we have today.\n\nThe creation of CWS, along with its sister schools (Neighborhood School, East Village Community School, Earth School and Tompkins Square Middle School) sparked interest from families throughout New York City and has contributed to their return to District 1. This is evidenced by our growing waiting lists, the number of families who have visited our schools as part of the choice process, and the increase in our student population every year. Our growth, however, has not hindered our commitment to maintaining a small progressive school, whose students possess a full range of racial, linguistic, and cultural heritages; income levels, and learning abilities. The population and staff of the school is growing, and because of strong parental involvement, we have been able to add many enrichment programs including music, dance, a school band, yoga and movement classes school-wide, a library program in our Library and Media Center, Turtle Bay Music classes, and an extensive afterschool clubs program.\n\nWe continue to enjoy a productive partnership with Manhattan Country School, including a weeklong Farm Program for our 4th graders and The Living the Dream Award, a joint project between both school\'s 5th graders. Our fifth grade class also goes to Washington D.C. every spring to observe and participate in the political process.\n\nIn December, we have a community craft fair, and a book fair to raise funds to maintain our beautiful library and its 10,000 volume collection.\nEvery spring, our school community hosts two celebrations; an Art &amp; Science Fair in May for the children and community, and our primary fundraising event Schoolapalooza; a food, entertainment, art and silent auction extravaganza for the parents and friends of the school. Lisa Lisa of Cult Jam fame always joins Schoolapalooza and rocks the house.','History','','publish','open','closed','','history','','','2012-09-25 06:48:42','2012-09-25 06:48:42','',189,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?page_id=191',0,'page','',0),(194,1,'2012-09-25 06:54:17','2012-09-25 06:54:17','<a title=\"Weekly Events\" href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/community/weekly-events/\">Weekly Community Meetings</a>, <a title=\"Turtle Bay Music School\" href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/aboutcws/programs/turtle-bay-music-school/\">Turtle Bay Music School Music Program and Chorus</a>; CWS Band Ensemble; Community Gardening Partnerships; <a title=\"The NiteStar Program\" href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/aboutcws/programs/the-nitestar-program/\">Nitestar Adolescent Education Program</a>; <a title=\"Bent On Learning\" href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/aboutcws/programs/bent-on-learning/\">Bent on Learning</a>; Alvin Ailey Movement Classes; Cookshop/Farm Boxes; Manhattan Country School Farm Program; New York University; Bank Street College.\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/cwsenrichments.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1137\" alt=\"cwsenrichments\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/cwsenrichments-550x699.jpg\" width=\"550\" height=\"699\" /></a>','Programs','','publish','open','open','','programs','','','2012-09-25 06:54:17','2012-09-25 06:54:17','',189,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?page_id=194',0,'page','',0),(198,1,'2012-09-25 06:59:26','2012-09-25 06:59:26','The Children\'s Workshop School, founded in 1993, is a progressive public elementary school located on the East Village of Manhattan. CWS strives for students to be open-minded and compassionate; to gain a sense of themselves and others; and to understand and appreciate the diversity of the community. Children are guided and supported to fulfill their creative, physical, emotional, social and intellectual potential. Our goal is for our children to recognize that they have the power and resources to effect change. It is our hope that children will grow to be responsible, critical and caring members of a pluralistic society.\n\nHonoring the Dream\nEvery January, we celebrate the vision and dream of Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr with an all-school concert that reaffirms our hope for a just and peaceful world. Teachers work with the students to develop class performances and every child has the opportunity to be a part of the presentation. We have the Honoring the Dream Celebration off-site to accommodate our growing CWS community. It is a moving and exhilarating experience and is open to the public.  ','Values','','publish','open','open','','values','','','2012-09-25 06:59:26','2012-09-25 06:59:26','',189,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?page_id=198',0,'page','',0),(200,1,'2012-09-25 07:06:01','2012-09-25 07:06:01','CWS Parent Teacher Association\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/pta/ptaimage/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-956\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-956\" title=\"PTAimage\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/PTAimage-550x123.jpeg\" width=\"550\" height=\"123\" /></a>\n\nBeing a Children\'s Workshop School parent means you are a part of a group called the Children\'s Workshop School Parent Teacher Association (CWSPTA). The  CWSPTA all work together to raise money for the school through fun events such as the Harvest Festival, Holiday Craft Fair, Arts and Science Fair and Schoolapalooza, and Tax Deductable donations.\n\nCWS has experienced nearly $500,000 in DOE budget cuts in the last four years including the loss of several teachers. Parents are being asked to fund their child\'s public education by replacing these lost funds which pay for the library, classroom supplies, all art and music programs, dance, computers, foreign language instruction, lice inspections, etc.\n\nThe PTA is always looking for help and fundraising opportunities so join the meetings and help CWS maintain its educational mission for your child. CWSPTA meetings are held once a month at the school. The meeting is your forum to voice opinion, discuss ideas and participate in our child\'s education.\n\nSee Calendar for meeting and fundraising opportunities!\n\nContact the PTA at<a href=\"mailto:PTA@childrensworkshopschool.org\"> PTAEB@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/CWSptainfo.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1140\" alt=\"CWSptainfo\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/CWSptainfo-550x711.jpg\" width=\"550\" height=\"711\" /></a>','About our PTA','','publish','open','open','','pta','','','2012-09-25 07:06:01','2012-09-25 07:06:01','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?page_id=200',0,'page','',0),(205,1,'2012-09-25 07:08:55','2012-09-25 07:08:55','<strong>Your 2013-14 PTA Executive Board Members</strong>\n\n<strong>Co-Presidents</strong>\n<div>\n\nBeth Counihan (BethC@childrensworkshopschool.org)\n\nRina Ortega (RinaO@childrensworkshopschool.org)\n\n<strong>Co-Vice Presidents</strong>\n\nHeidi Hynes (Heidi@childrensworkshopschool.org)\n\nElizabeth Downer (Elizabeth@childrensworkshopschool.org)\n\n</div>\n<strong>Co-Treasurers</strong>\n\nKeiko Hirosue (Keiko@childrensworkshopschool.org)\n\nShay Singh (ShayS@childrensworkshopschool.org)\n<strong> Co-Secretaries</strong>\n\nTiffany Zerges (tiffany@childrensworkshopschool.org)\n\nMo Wu ( mow@childrensworkshopschool.org)\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;','Board Members','','publish','open','open','','boardmembers','','','2012-09-25 07:08:55','2012-09-25 07:08:55','',200,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?page_id=205',0,'page','',0),(206,1,'2012-09-25 07:09:10','2012-09-25 07:09:10','','ANNOUNCEMENTS','','publish','open','open','','announcements','','','2012-09-25 07:09:10','2012-09-25 07:09:10','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?page_id=206',0,'page','',0),(211,1,'2012-09-25 07:12:45','2012-09-25 07:12:45','<span class=\"CommunityText\">No matter what committee you choose, please get involved as an active participant in our community and your children\'s education. Some committees have a bulletin board/announcements. Click on the title of the teams to go to their individual activity pages.</span>\n<table width=\"600\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"CommunityTextBold\"><strong>School Leadership Team:</strong></td>\n<td width=\"567\"><span class=\"CommunityText\">Participate in meetings with school faculty and administration to discuss and advise on CWS curriculum and policy. Meets once a month. <a href=\"mailto:slt@childrensworkshopschool.org\">slt@childrensworkshopschool.org</a></span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"CommunityTextBold\"><strong>Nutrition Committee:</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"CommunityText\">Work with all three schools building-wide to discuss and advise on nutritional issues. Meets once a month. Chair: Leslie Rodgers (<a href=\"mailto:Nutrition@childrensworkshopschool.org\">Nutrition@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>)</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"CommunityTextBold\" width=\"223\"><strong>Technology Committee:</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"CommunityText\">Work on steering technology efforts, obtaining grants to fund technology initiatives; responsible for school website and communications.  Chairs: Ian and Keiko. Meets once a month. Contacts: Web related: <a href=\"mailto:web@childrensworkshopschool.org\">web@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>, <a href=\"mailto:IanJ@childrensworkshopschool.org\">Ian@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>,  Entire Tech Team: <a href=\"mailto:cwstechteam@gmail.com\">cwstechteam@gmail.com</a></span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"CommunityTextBold\"><strong>Building &amp; GYM Committee:</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"CommunityText\">Work on efforts to improve our facilities, obtain grants for capital improvements, liaison with government agencies for funding and information.  Knowledge of construction industry, architecture, or legal a huge plus. Chairs: Dorothy Cantwell (<a href=\"mailto:ptcoordinator@childrensworkshopschool.org\">ptcoordinator@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>)  &amp; Melissa Vigilante (<a href=\"mailto:Melissa@childrensworkshopschool.org\">Melissa@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>)</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"CommunityTextBold\"><strong>Fundraising &amp; Grant Writing Committee:</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"CommunityText\">Work on writing grants, creating fundraising initiatives, corporate and community outreach,  etc. to offset budget cuts and assist PTA in funding initiatives.  Includes Friday hospitality efforts during community meeting with donations of refreshments. Committee Chair: Melissa Vigilante (<a href=\"mailto:Melissa@childrensworkshopschool.org\">Melissa@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>)</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"CommunityTextBold\"><a title=\"Harvest Festival Committee\" href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/category/committees-harvestfestival/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Harvest Festival:</strong></a></td>\n<td><span class=\"CommunityText\">Assist with organizing the fun event celebrating the harvest. Revived in 2012. (Saturday, October 13, 2012). Contact: <a href=\"mailto:julie@childrensworkshopschool.org\">ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org</a> Chair: Julie Stark and Elizabeth Downer</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"CommunityTextBold\"><strong>Holiday Craft Fair:</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"CommunityText\">Assist with largest winter fundraising event by obtaining vendors, organizing donations, organizing manpower, etc.  (Friday, December 7, 2012). Contact: <a href=\"mailto:holidaycrafts@childrensworkshopschool.org\">holidaycrafts@childrensworkshopschool.org</a> Chair: Bari Franklin</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"CommunityTextBold\"><a title=\"Schoolapalooza\" href=\"http://www.schoola.org/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Schoolapalooza:</strong></a></td>\n<td><span class=\"CommunityText\">Plan our biggest fundraiser (March 2013)   Early start-up a must for outreach to businesses and community for  donation.  Help with art auction, silent auction, food, entertainment, etc. Chair:  Ian Jelinek Contact:  <a href=\"mailto:schoolapa@childrensworkshopschool.org\">schoolapa@childrensworkshopschool.org</a></span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"CommunityTextBold\"><strong>Library Committee:</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"CommunityText\">Work to support the administration of our 10,000 volume library.  Must commit to one day a week minimum. Contact: Dorothy Cantwell (<a href=\"mailto:ptcoordinator@childrensworkshopschool.org\">ptcoordinator@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>)</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"CommunityTextBold\"><strong>Art &amp; Science Fair:</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"CommunityText\">A spring event on the day before Mother’s Day that celebrates our kids, our families, our teachers, the sciences, the arts, and our unique and vibrant community (May 11, 2013). Chair: Judy Garner-Wortzel (<a href=\"mailto:JudyG@childrensworkshopschool.org\">JudyG@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>)</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"CommunityTextBold\"><strong>Book Fair:</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"CommunityText\">Work on Fall’s event with Barnes and Noble in Union Square which raises money to run the library and expand the book collection. (Around December 15, 2012) Chair: Melissa (<a href=\"mailto:MelissaV@childrensworkshopschool.org\">Melissa@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>) </span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"CommunityTextBold\"><strong>Hair Specialist:</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"CommunityText\">Help LiceLogic in administering lice detection program during outbreaks with sensitivity and efficiency. As needed basis. Chair: Nancy (<a href=\"mailto:NancyM@childrensworkshopschool.org\">NancyM@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>)</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"CommunityTextBold\"><strong>Advocacy Committee:</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"CommunityText\">Keep abreast of local, state, and national policies that will affect our children’s education, our city, and our school. Be a public advocate for CWS. Last year’s activities included protests on budget cuts in Tompkin’s Square Park, and in front of the mayor’s office. Chair: Hope Baker(<a href=\"mailto:advocacy@childrensworkshopschool.org\">advocacy@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>)</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"CommunityTextBold\"><strong>Original Works Coordinator:</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"CommunityText\">Administer and coordinate with teachers and classrooms for this fundraiser which takes the children’s artwork and creates products and gifts.  Organize the sale and distribution of finished products. (November, April) Chair:  Jennifer Wilson (<a href=\"mailto:JenniferW@childrensworkshopschool.org\">JenniferW@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>)  </span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"CommunityTextBold\"><strong>Gardening &amp; Greening Committee:</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"CommunityText\">Work to green our school through supporting and expanding our farm-box program, cooking classes, community outreach efforts, recycling, etc. There will be a Harvest Festival on October 13, 2012. Chair: Leslie Rodgers (<a href=\"mailto:Julie@childrensworkshopschool.org\">Leslie@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>) </span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"CommunityTextBold\"><strong>Videography/Photo Committee:</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"CommunityText\">Work on documenting all-school events such as Friday Community Meetings, special performances, MLK Celebration; produce recordings for resale to parents.  Preferably someone with equipment. Material costs will be covered.</span><span class=\"BoldIntroText_AdminOrange\">**Need Committee Chair!**</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"CommunityTextBold\"><strong>SCRIP Gift Cards:</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"CommunityText\">Coordinate the sale of gift cards in December and May for stores and services (everything from Amazon.com to Exxon)--the merchants donate 1-15% of the gift card amounts to CWS.  Chair: Helen Chan (<a href=\"mailto:helenc@childrensworkshopschool.org\">HelenC@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>)</span></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>','Committees','','publish','open','open','','committees','','','2012-09-25 07:12:45','2012-09-25 07:12:45','',200,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?page_id=211',0,'page','',0),(215,1,'2012-09-25 07:18:18','2012-09-25 07:18:18','Class parents assist the teacher in communicating class needs and fundraising initiatives to families.  They are the point-person for parents and also facilitate communication between the PTA and CWS families.  They are chosen at the beginning of the year with a maximum of three parents per classroom. Please discuss with your teacher if you would like to volunteer!\n\nYou can always communicate with our CWS PTA Communication Director here: <a href=\"mailto:ian@childrensworkshopschool.org\">ian@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>\n\n&nbsp;','Class Parents','','publish','open','open','','classparents','','','2012-09-25 07:18:18','2012-09-25 07:18:18','',200,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?page_id=215',0,'page','',0),(217,1,'2012-09-25 07:19:38','2012-09-25 07:19:38','We will be posting Meeting Logs from our PTA meetings here. Please click on the month to download a PDF&gt;\n\nSeptember 2013\n\nOctober 2013\n\nNovember 2013\n\nDecember 2013\n\nJanuary 2014\n\nFebruary 2014\n\nMarch 2014\n\nApril 2014\n\nMay 2014\n\nJune 2014','Meeting Logs','','publish','open','open','','meetinglogs','','','2012-09-25 07:19:38','2012-09-25 07:19:38','',200,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?page_id=217',0,'page','',0),(221,1,'2012-09-25 07:20:55','2012-09-25 07:20:55','PTA proudly supports:\n<ul>\n	<li><a title=\"Turtle Bay Music School\" href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/aboutcws/programs/turtle-bay-music-school/\">Turtle Bay Music School Music Program and Chorus</a></li>\n	<li><a title=\"Bent On Learning\" href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/aboutcws/programs/bent-on-learning/\">Bent on Learning</a></li>\n	<li>CWS Band Ensemble</li>\n	<li><a title=\"The NiteStar Program\" href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/aboutcws/programs/the-nitestar-program/\">NiteStar Adolescent Education Program</a></li>\n	<li>Manhattan Country School Farm Program</li>\n	<li>Washington D.C. Trip</li>\n	<li>5th Grade Graduation &amp; Year Books</li>\n	<li>Teacher Development      and more!</li>\n</ul>\nWe also encourage and help bring in programs such as Farm Box initiative as part of the <a href=\"http://www.foodbanknyc.org/index.cfm?objectid=F428F9C1-3048-651A-200410818924E347\">CookShop program</a>.\n\nIn the past, we have funded Alvin Ailey Movement Classes and Ballet Hispanico.','PTA Funded Programs','','publish','open','open','','pta-funded-programs','','','2012-09-25 07:20:55','2012-09-25 07:20:55','',200,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?page_id=221',0,'page','',0),(223,1,'2012-09-25 07:22:42','2012-09-25 07:22:42','– to those who support the school by donating to the PTA Pledge Drive\n– to those who support the school by using Book Fair Coupons at Barnes and Noble this Holiday Season\n– to those who make the Holiday Crafts Fair  wonderful by setting up, selling, donating items, doing their Holiday Shopping with us.\n– to all who make Honoring the Dream come true\n– to those of you who brought us Schoolapalooza,  planning, collecting items, gift certificates, tickets and more great stuff for the Schoolapalooza Silent Auction\n– to Judy Garnar-Wortzel and all the volunteers and guests at The Art and Science Fair, which is always a fantastic family day\n– to those who support our Parent Hospitality Events like Coffee and... and classroom writing celebrations, Family Visits and Multicultural Events\n– to those who attend Community meetings, performances like the Talent Show, Tada! and Ballet Hispanico and CWS Band Concerts\n– to those who participate in parent/child  projects and fundraisers like Original Works and The CWS Peace Labyrinth.\n– to those serve on standing PTA committees like the Garden, Nutrition, and Building Committees\n– to those who bring great ideas to the PTA and SLT like Bent on Learning Yoga and Farm Box/CookShop\n– to those who serve as officers on the PTA Executive Board and the SLT\n– to Rosie Kanellis for being the unofficial graphic designer at CWS, 2012\n– to Claire McConaughy who designed the base of this website, 2011\n– to Creative Web Solutions who constructed the wordpress website together with CWS Tech Team, 2012','Thanks For All You Do','','publish','open','open','','thanks-for-all-you-do','','','2012-09-25 07:22:42','2012-09-25 07:22:42','',200,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?page_id=223',0,'page','',0),(263,1,'2012-09-25 07:58:54','2012-09-25 07:58:54','Not today? We understand. Thank you for considering donating.\n\nCWS is striving to maintain our arts, music, dance, math, computer and science classes and uphold or mission of creating world citizens in the face of continuous and brutal budget cuts. Every little bit helps with our goal . . . and donating time is as important as donating money.\n\nContact the <a href=\"mailto:ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org\">PTA</a> and volunteer to help out our school.\n\nWe are also always available at the office on the second floor. We accept checks written out to CWS PTA for any amount that you feel comfortable with. We also have a credit card reader, and can swipe you on the spot.\n\nYou can also donate by clicking the button below, directly through our Paypal, using your Credit Card or Debit Card. We also set up an easy recurring donation option. For the school to maintain and fund all the programs that we are fortunate to have in the school, we would really appreciate your contribution. Thank you!\n\n<form action=\"https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr\" method=\"post\"><input type=\"hidden\" name=\"cmd\" value=\"_s-xclick\" />\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"hosted_button_id\" value=\"T42PDGTAWPDCQ\" />\n<input type=\"image\" name=\"submit\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/donate_btn.jpg\" alt=\"PayPal - The safer, easier way to pay online!\" />\n<img src=\"https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/scr/pixel.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" border=\"0\" /></form><form action=\"https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr\" method=\"post\"><input type=\"hidden\" name=\"cmd\" value=\"_s-xclick\" /><input type=\"hidden\" name=\"hosted_button_id\" value=\"PEJPBTSGY54AN\" />\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><input type=\"hidden\" name=\"on0\" value=\"Monthly Donation Options\" />Monthly Donation Options</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><select name=\"os0\"> <option value=\"1: I will donate\">1: I will donate $50.00 monthly</option> <option value=\"2: I will donate\">2: I will donate $75.00 monthly</option> <option selected=\"selected\" value=\"3: I will donate\">3: I will donate $100.00 monthly</option> <option value=\"4: I will donate\">4: I will donate $200.00 monthly</option> <option value=\"5: I will donate\">5: I will donate $300.00 monthly</option> </select></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"currency_code\" value=\"USD\" />\n<input type=\"image\" name=\"submit\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/recurring.jpg\" alt=\"PayPal - The safer, easier way to pay online!\" /><img src=\"https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/scr/pixel.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" border=\"0\" />\n\n</form>Thank you so much for your contribution and supporting public education and CWS! Contact the PTA and volunteer to help out our school. If you need assistance with your paypal transactions, please contact <a href=\"mailto:donations@childrensworkshopschool.org\">donations@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>. We are always looking to partner with our community and businesses to make CWS the best school that it can be. Thank you in advance for your donation and interest. CWS kids rock!','Not Today? We understand.','','publish','open','open','','cancel','','','2012-09-25 07:58:54','2012-09-25 07:58:54','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?page_id=263',0,'page','',0),(331,1,'2012-09-26 20:51:28','2012-09-26 20:51:28','<strong>Thank you for interest in The Children\'s Workshop!</strong>\n\n<strong></strong>\nDistrict One is a District of Choice so parents are not limited to the zoned school and we encourage you to visit, hear an overview of the curriculum, observe our classrooms, and ask questions. <a title=\"School Tours\" href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/admissions/school-tours/\">School Tours</a> are scheduled from October to March and you will need to reserve a spot. Parents interested in Pre-k and K admissions for September 2015 should call \nJoyce at (212) 614-9531 ext 2091 or E-mail jborden@schools.nyc.gov \nor Dorothy Ext 4081 E-mail DCantwell2@schools.nyc.gov.\n\nWatch this spot for school tour schedules  \n\nIf you are interesed in other grades or September 2014 admission\nplease E-mail Dorothy. School is not in session in the summer, but we will try to arrange a time to meet with you, answer your questions and register your child.  \n\n&nbsp;\n\nThe actual application process for and is conducted by the DOE so please follow this link to learn about the process.\n\n<a href=\"http://schools.nyc.gov/ChoicesEnrollment/default.htm\" target=\"_blank\">NYC Department of Education Student Enrollment</a>','ADMISSIONS','','publish','open','open','','admissions','','','2012-09-26 20:51:28','2012-09-26 20:51:28','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?page_id=331',0,'page','',0),(425,1,'2012-09-13 03:25:31','2012-09-13 03:25:31','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/community/afterschool-clubs/afterschool/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-793\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-793\" title=\"afterschool\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/afterschool-300x163.jpeg\" width=\"300\" height=\"163\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">mural club 2012</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img title=\"2013-04-20 09.52.50\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/2013-04-20-09.52.50-300x300.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /> <a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/community/afterschool-clubs/2013-04-20-09-49-53/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-947\"><img title=\"2013-04-20 09.49.53\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/2013-04-20-09.49.53-300x300.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a><a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/community/afterschool-clubs/2013-04-20-09-52-50/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-948\">\n</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Dance Improvisation Club 2013</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?attachment_id=1326\">CLICK HERE &gt;&gt;&gt; FOR FALL clubs 2014 BROCHURE</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Dear Parents,\nWelcome to a new session of after school clubs! Please take time to read this letter and the clubs list, as there is some new information.\nREGISTRATION WILL BE HELD IN THE LOBBY FROM 7:45AM TO 9:00am ON TWO REGISTRATION DAYS. Date to TBA for Fall 2014-15.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">THERE WILL BE NO BREAK IN BETWEEN FALL AND SPRING CLUBS.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Remember: In order to cover the club\'s expenses, each club MUST have a minimum of 7 children in order for the club to run. Once again, PLEASE FILL OUT ALL NECESSARY FORMS BEFORE COMING TO REGISTRATION. THIS IS EXTREMELY IMPORTANT! This will help the registration process move more quickly.This year, we will add an extra week onto each semester of clubs making each club last 19 weeks instead of 17 as in the past, in order to offer clubs earlier in Mid-September and later in June to accommodate busy parents. Because of that and increasing costs, all clubs will cost $260 for the 19 sessions which makes the cost for each session $13.70. Some clubs require a $10 or $20 materials fee. We will offer a 20% discount to those enrolling in 4 or more clubs.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">MAKE CHECKS PAYABLE TO <span style=\"color: #0000ff;\">THE CWS PTA</span>. WE ACCEPT CREDIT CARDS AS WELL. DO NOT HAND IN REGISTRATION FORMS TO THE OFFICE! <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">There will be a lottery for clubs that are over enrolled so there is no need to worry about being first at registration.</span> Parents may register for the children of ONE other family in addition to their own. So, if you are unable to make registration for whatever reason, you may ask another parent to register your children for you. A list of the clubs will be displayed at registration so parents will be able to see which clubs are full and which have spaces left.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">As ever, no one should hesitate to join a club for lack of money. If your family needs assistance, contact me or Maria Velez-Clarke. If you have any questions or concerns, you may contact Joyce in the office.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Snack will be provided to all children right after school. Parents or caretakers should pick up their children promptly at 4:45 in the lobby. Please be on time! Club leaders have to leave promptly at 4:45. You also have the option of putting your child in the <a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/EXTENDED-LETTER-FALL-2012.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">extended day option</a> and pick your child up any time between 4:45 and 5:50pm. Clubs do not meet on half days, school holidays, and parent teacher conference days.<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/EXTENDED-LETTER-FALL-2012.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"> (Click here for detailed pricing for Extended Day&gt;&gt;).</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">We are also very pleased to announce that our school secretary, Joyce Borden, and Rachael Frank, a CWS parent will be helping again with the clubs program this year. Many programs are also taught by the CWS teachers and parents. Thank you so much for all the support!</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">For alternative options there is \"Green Apple Kids\" that host afterschool programs in the Earth School. They will provide after school, half days and holiday days programming for the coming school year. The program focuses on health, wellness and environmental education. The children will learn about themselves and the world around them through, theater, cooking, gardening, mindfulness practices and varied types of movement exercises. In addition to the directed learning at after school there will be time for snack and homework tutoring (if needed) and free play. At the full day sessions when we provide time for snack, lunch, out door play time, trips and or special activities. The Green Apple Kids curriculum is child-centered and strives to engage all children at their comfort level.</p>\n&nbsp;\n\nGreen Apple Kids will pick up from CWS and EVCS for a monthly fee of $20. They offer 5 days, 4 days, 3 day, 2 day and 1 day care options.\n\nTo register please email <a href=\"mailto:greenapplekidsny@gmail.com\">greenapplekidsny@gmail.com</a> or call 347-497-0732\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"></p>','Afterschool Clubs','','publish','open','open','','afterschool-clubs','','','2012-09-13 03:25:31','2012-09-13 03:25:31','',344,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?page_id=425',0,'page','',0),(652,1,'2012-01-30 09:00:52','2012-01-30 14:00:52','With the help of a parent at CWS, we have invited an orchestra; Die Telemanner from Germany to visit NYC. We hosted the students and staff, welcomed them to our families\' homes, and attended their concerts that happened in several locations during their stay. We hope this will be the beginning of the cultural exchange.\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/german_orchestra1.jpg\"><img title=\"german_orchestra\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/german_orchestra1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"268\" height=\"197\" /></a>\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/German_orchestra_flyer.pdf\">German_orchestra_flyer</a>\n\n<iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/63hjkPVTtEI\" frameborder=\"0\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\"></iframe>','Die Telemänner in CWS','','publish','open','open','','die-telemanner-in-cws','','','2012-01-30 09:00:52','2012-01-30 14:00:52','',355,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?page_id=652',0,'page','',0),(334,1,'2012-09-26 20:55:00','2012-09-26 20:55:00','<em><strong>Families interested in The Children’s Workshop School, please email Joyce  (<a href=\"mailto:jborden@schools.nyc.gov\" target=\"_blank\">jborden@schools.nyc.gov</a>) or c<em><strong>all  Joyce at (212) 614-9531  Ext 2091</strong></em>to sign up for a school tour starting in late September. Any questions about Pre-K admission for Fall 2015, or 2014 placements in other grades as well, please contact Joyce. </strong></em>\n\nAll tours start at 8:15 am and will go on until 9:30am.\n\nOctober 21, November 18, December 2, December 16, January 6, January 20, February 3, February 24\n\n<em><strong>We look forward to meeting you!</strong></em>\n\nPlease come on time.\n\nPlease visit the <a href=\"http://schools.nyc.gov/ChoicesEnrollment/default.htm\" target=\"_blank\">DOE website</a> for more information on Admissions for Kindergarten and Pre-K. Admissions for all other grade levels will be handled at the school level, as District One is a District of Choice. Parents are not limited to the zoned school and we encourage you to visit, hear an overview of the curriculum, observe our classrooms, and ask questions. Please inquire about availability in upper grades when you come to the school for a tour.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/CWSOpenHouseFlyerFall2014.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1345\" alt=\"CWSOpenHouseFlyerFall2014\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/CWSOpenHouseFlyerFall2014-550x729.jpg\" width=\"550\" height=\"729\" /></a>','School Tours','','publish','open','open','','school-tours','','','2012-09-26 20:55:00','2012-09-26 20:55:00','',331,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?page_id=334',0,'page','',0),(344,1,'2012-09-26 21:47:07','2012-09-26 21:47:07','','COMMUNITY','','publish','open','open','','community','','','2012-09-26 21:47:07','2012-09-26 21:47:07','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?page_id=344',0,'page','',0),(346,1,'2012-09-26 21:17:49','2012-09-26 21:17:49','<strong>Coffee And...</strong>\nFriday mornings are for coffee and community. Come join us for coffee, donated baked goods, good company and our weekly community meeting lead by Gary, our art teacher. Community meeting could be songs, stories, or performances by the kids. Friday also features a Book Sale, CWS goods sale, or the Theme Fridays to fund our 5th graders\' annual trip to Washington D.C.. It is a great way to meet other parents, enjoy wonderful food, and support The Children\'s Workshop School. Contact Melissa Vigilante, our Fundraising and Grant writing Committee chair at <a href=\"mailto:melissa@childrensworkshopschool.org\">melissa@childrensworkshopschool.org</a> to help out or to bake.\n\nThank you to the Porto Rico Import Company for their generous and delicious donation of coffee every year. Don’t miss the social event of the week.\n\n<strong>Community Meetings</strong>\nOne of the places that Children’s Workshop School families, children and teachers come together is at Community Meeting. Beginning in October, on Friday mornings, starting 9am sharp, families and friends are invited to join the children in the lobby while the auditorium is under construction. During Community Meeting, classes share performances, outside guests present special programs, students and teachers share poetry and stories... anything can happen. Most importantly, we come together as a joyful group to celebrate our unique, multi-talented and loving CWS family. Every Community Meeting ends with a rousing sing-along of our favorite songs, led by our Arts teacher...the one and only Gary Morston, Grand Griot, Storyteller and Songmeister.\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/community/weekly-events/photo-1-2/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1016\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-1016 alignleft\" title=\"photo (1)\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/photo-1-550x550.jpg\" alt=\"New Auditorium\" width=\"550\" height=\"550\" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/DSCN2252.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-585\" title=\"DSCN2252\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/DSCN2252-550x412.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"412\" /></a>\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/CommunityMeetingLobbyOct2012.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-567\" title=\"CommunityMeetingLobbyOct2012\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/CommunityMeetingLobbyOct2012-550x550.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"550\" /></a>','Weekly Events','','publish','open','open','','weekly-events','','','2012-09-26 21:17:49','2012-09-26 21:17:49','',344,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?page_id=346',0,'page','',0),(1433,1,'2014-12-23 14:04:40','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-23 14:04:40','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://192.168.59.103/?p=1433',0,'post','',0),(1435,1,'2014-12-23 14:50:54','2014-12-23 19:50