-the-willow-tree','','','2010-11-12 09:00:45','2010-11-12 09:00:45','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=134',0,'post','',0),(141,1,'2007-06-15 09:00:02','2007-06-15 09:00:02','Elizabeth Jennings Place\nChildren\'s Workshop Students are not \"waiting on the world to change...\" They are doing their best to change it themselves.. They are taking what they have learned and sharing information and their message outside of the school.  Teacher Miriam Sicherman\'s class saw the success of their year long research and advocacy when they unveiled the new street sign for Elizabeth Jennings Place. Councilman Alan Gerson was instrumental in supporting the student\'s efforts. Chancellor Joel Klein joined the CWS community as they celebrated their permanent history lesson for the City of New York! <a href=\"http://204.42.140.58/archives/newsjune07/jennings.htm\" target=\"_blank\">Read the article here&gt;&gt;</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/maria.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-97\" title=\"maria\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/maria.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"422\" height=\"333\" /></a><a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/group.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-142\" title=\"group\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/group.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"520\" height=\"333\" /></a>','6/15/2007 CWS In the Tribeca Trib','','publish','open','open','','6152007-cws-in-the-tribeca-trib','','','2007-06-15 09:00:02','2007-06-15 09:00:02','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=141',0,'post','',0),(543,1,'2012-10-10 00:49:38','0000-00-00 00:00:00','Permalink under the title shows how it will look like on the browser. You can edit if the title gets long.\n\nText Body is here.\n\nJust like microsoft word.\n\nYou can click on the buttons above to see what it does.\n\nthe one thing, is the BLOCK QUOTE: